exercise.name: Cable Neck Flexion
exercise.execution: Move head away from pulley by bending neck forward until chin touches upper chest. Return head by hyperextending neck and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Neck Flexion (with belt)
exercise.execution: Pull head forward and down by flexing neck until chin touches upper chest. Return by hyperextending neck until head is angled upward. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Neck Rotation (with belt)
exercise.execution: Turn head away from pulley cable by rotating head away from pulley. Turn head back toward cable pulley and repeat. Turn seat the opposite direction or attach belt to pulley on opposite side and continue with other side.

exercise.name: Cable Lateral Neck Flexion (with belt)
exercise.execution: Pull head away from pulley cable by laterally flexing neck. Tilt head back toward cable pulley and repeat. Sit on bench the opposite direction and continue with other side.

exercise.name: Lever Neck Flexion (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Move head forward by flexing neck until chin touches upper chest. Return head by hyperextending neck and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Lateral Neck Flexion (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Move head down to side by laterally flexing neck. Return head to opposite side and repeat. Sit in machine backwards and continue with opposite side.

exercise.name: Lever Neck Flexion
exercise.execution: Move head forward by flexing neck until chin touches upper chest. Return head by hyperextending neck and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Lateral Neck Flexion
exercise.execution: Move head down to side by laterally flexing neck. Return head to opposite side and repeat. Sit in machine backwards and continue with opposite side.

exercise.name: Weighted Lying Neck Flexion
exercise.execution: Move head up by flexing neck until chin touches upper chest. Return by hyperextending neck and repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Neck Flexion
exercise.execution: Move head up by flexing neck until chin touches upper chest. Return by hyperextending neck and repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Lateral Neck Flexion
exercise.execution: Move head up to side by laterally flexing neck. Lower head to opposite side and repeat. Lie on other side and continue.

exercise.name: Front Neck Bridge
exercise.execution: Roll back onto forehead until nose touches mat. Roll forward onto top of head until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Wall Front Neck Bridge
exercise.execution: Roll down onto forehead until nose touches mat. Roll up onto top of head until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Wall Side Neck Bridge
exercise.execution: Push side of head into mat and roll onto top of head moving body away from mat. Return to original position by rolling back down to side of head while bringing shoulder back over end of column or wall. Repeat.

exercise.name: Neck Retraction Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Pull head back as far possible while looking slightly down and hold stretch.

exercise.name: Neck Rotation Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Turn head over shoulder to one side. Hold stretch. Repeat to other side.

exercise.name: Suspended Neck Flexion
exercise.execution: Increase angle of body by bowing head until chin touches upper chest. Lower angle of body by raising head. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Lateral Neck Flexion
exercise.execution: Lower angle of body by tilting head to side of suspension trainer. Increase angle of body by tilting head away from side of suspension trainer. Repeat and continue in opposite position.

exercise.name: Cable Neck Extension
exercise.execution: Move head away from pulley by hyperextending neck. Return by bending neck forward until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Neck Extension (with belt)
exercise.execution: Pull head up and back by hyperextending neck. Return by bending neck forward until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Neck Extension (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Move head back by hyperextending neck. Return by bending neck forward until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Neck Extension
exercise.execution: Move head back by hyperextending neck. Return by bending neck forward until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Lying Neck Extension
exercise.execution: Move head up by hyperextending neck up as high as possible. Return by bending neck down until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Neck Extension
exercise.execution: Move head up by hyperextending neck up as high as possible. Return by bending neck down until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Seated Neck Extension
exercise.execution: Move head up by hyperextending neck up as high as possible. Return by bending neck down until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Neck Harness Extension
exercise.execution: Move head up by hyperextending neck. Return by bending neck down until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Rear Neck Bridge
exercise.execution: Extend hips and knees while pushing head back into floor. Roll back on head while arching spine high off of floor. Hyperextend neck back in attempt to bring forehead toward mat. Return body to close to mat until back of head and shoulders make contact with mat. Repeat.

exercise.name: Wall Rear Neck Bridge
exercise.execution: Hold small or folded cushioned mat behind head. Facing away from wall or column position head and back of shoulders low on wall or column with mat between. Stand with feet far away from wall or column so body is angled back. Position hips and back straight and bend knees just slightly. Place arms to side or hold hands on abdomen.

exercise.name: Neck Extensor Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Slightly turn head to one side. Hold stretch. Repeat to other side.

exercise.name: Suspended Neck Extension
exercise.execution: Place belt or strap around end of suspension trainer. Place belt around head above ears and clamp belt snugly around head by tightly gripping ends close to forehead. Step back facing direction of suspension trainer until it is taut. Lean back at angle against support of belt and suspension trainer by stepping forward slightly while keeping head and body straight.

exercise.name: Plow Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Allow knees to drop toward floor to sides of head. Hold stretch.

exercise.name: Barbell Behind Neck Press
exercise.execution: Press bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Return behind neck and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Front Raise
exercise.execution: Raise barbell forward and upward until upper arms are above horizontal. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Incline Front Raise
exercise.execution: With elbows straight or slightly bent, raise barbell up and over shoulders until uppers arm are vertical. Lower barbell to upper thigh and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Military Press
exercise.execution: Press bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower to front of neck and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Seated Military Press
exercise.execution: Press bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Return to upper chest and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Shoulder Press
exercise.execution: Press bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Return to upper chest and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Reclined Shoulder Press
exercise.execution: Press bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Return to upper chest and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Bar Behind Neck Press
exercise.execution: Press cable bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Return behind neck and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Bar Front Raise
exercise.execution: Raise cable bar forward and upward until upper arms are above horizontal. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Bar Military Press
exercise.execution: Press cable bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Return to upper chest and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Bar Shoulder Press
exercise.execution: Press cable bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Return to upper chest and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Seated Front Raise
exercise.execution: Raise stirrups forward and upward until upper arms are well above horizontal. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Alternating Front Raise
exercise.execution: Raise one stirrup forward and upward until upper arm is well above horizontal. Lower and repeat with opposite arm, alternating between arms.

exercise.name: Cable Alternating Seated Front Raise
exercise.execution: Raise one stirrup forward and upward until upper arm is well above horizontal. Lower and repeat with opposite arm. Continue by alternating raises between sides.

exercise.name: Cable One Arm Front Raise
exercise.execution: Raise stirrup forward and upward until upper arm is well above horizontal. Lower and repeat. Repeat with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Cable One Arm Front Raise (with rope)
exercise.execution: Raise stirrup forward and upward until arm is well above horizontal or cable makes contact with underside of upper arm. Lower and repeat. Repeat with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Cable Standing Shoulder Press
exercise.execution: Push stirrups upward until arms are extended overhead. Return stirrups to sides of shoulders and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Shoulder Press
exercise.execution: Push stirrups upward until arms are extended overhead. Return stirrups to sides of shoulders and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Twisting Overhead Press
exercise.execution: Rotate body away from pulley and straighten legs while pushing stirrup diagonally upward toward opposite side of body. Return to original position and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Arnold Press
exercise.execution: Initiate movement by bringing elbows out to sides. Continue to raise elbows outward while pressing dumbbells overhead until arms are straight. Lower to front of shoulders in opposite pattern and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Front Raise
exercise.execution: Raise dumbbells forward and upward until upper arms are above horizontal. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Alternating Front Raise
exercise.execution: Raise one dumbbell forward and upward with palms positioned downward until upper arm is above horizontal. Lower and repeat with opposite arm, alternating between arms.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Alternating Incline Front Raise
exercise.execution: With elbows straight or slightly bent, raise one dumbbell forward, up and over shoulder until upper arm is vertical. Lower dumbbell down to starting position. Repeat raise with other arm, alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Alternating Seated Front Raise
exercise.execution: Raise one dumbbell forward and upward while turning palms downward as soon as dumbbell clears thigh. Continue raising dumbbell until upper arm is above horizontal. Lower and turn palms inward while dumbbells travels past thigh until arm is in original vertical position. Repeat with opposite arm, alternating movement pattern between arms.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Alternating Full Can Seated Front Raise
exercise.execution: Raise one dumbbell forward and upward until upper arm is above horizontal. Lower to original vertical position. Repeat with opposite arm, alternating movement pattern between arms.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Seated Front Raise
exercise.execution: Raise dumbbells forward and upward while turning palms downward as soon as dumbbells clear thighs. Continue raising dumbbells until upper arms are above horizontal. Lower dumbbells and turn palms inward while dumbbells travels past thighs until arms are in original vertical position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Full Can Seated Front Raise
exercise.execution: Raise dumbbells forward and upward until upper arms are above horizontal. Lower to original vertical position and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Shoulder Press
exercise.execution: Press dumbbells upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower to sides of shoulders and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell One Arm Shoulder Press
exercise.execution: Press dumbbell upward until arm is extended overhead. Lower to side of shoulder and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Reclined Shoulder Press
exercise.execution: Press dumbbells upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower to sides of upper chest and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Behind Neck Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Press levers upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Barbell Behind Neck Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Press bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower bar behind neck and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Military Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Press lever until arms are extended upward. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Reclined Shoulder Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Press lever until arms are extended. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Shoulder Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Press lever upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Barbell Shoulder Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Press bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower bar to front of shoulders and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever One Arm Shoulder Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Press end of barbell upward and forward until arm is extended. Lower to shoulder and repeat. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Lever One Arm Front Raise
exercise.execution: Raise lever handle forward and upward until upper arm is well above horizontal. Lower and repeat. Repeat with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Lever Reclined Shoulder Press
exercise.execution: Press lever until arms are extended. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Reclined Parallel Grip Shoulder Press
exercise.execution: Press lever until arms are extended. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Shoulder Press
exercise.execution: Press lever upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Shoulder Press (parallel grip)
exercise.execution: Press lever upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Alternating Shoulder Press
exercise.execution: Press one lever upward until arm is extended overhead. Lower to original position. Repeat with opposite arm. Continue by alternating movement between arms.

exercise.name: Sled Shoulder Press
exercise.execution: Press handles upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Shoulder Press (parallel grip)
exercise.execution: Press handles upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Behind Neck Press
exercise.execution: Press bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower bar behind neck and repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Shoulder Press
exercise.execution: Press bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower bar to front of shoulders and repeat.

exercise.name: Handstand Push-up (between benches)
exercise.execution: Lower head between ends of benches by bending arms. Push body back up to original position by extending arms. Repeat.

exercise.name: Handstand Push-up (on parallettes)
exercise.execution: While maintaining body balanced over bars, push inverted body up by extending arms until straight. Lower body down by bending arms until shoulders are close to bars. Repeat.

exercise.name: Pike Press
exercise.execution: Lower head between ends of benches by bending arms. Push body back up to original position by extending arms. Repeat.

exercise.name: Elevated Pike Press
exercise.execution: Lower head between ends of benches by bending arms. Push body back up to original position by extending arms. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Front Raise
exercise.execution: Raise arms upward overhead by flexing shoulders with arms straight. Return and lower body back until arms are extended straight forward in original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Doorway Front Deltoid Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Turn body away from positioned arm. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Lying Front Deltoid Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Roll body onto right side by pushing left hand onto floor. Positioning bent left leg over straight right leg until stretch is felt. Hold stretch. Repeat in opposite position.

exercise.name: Seated Front Deltoid Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Scoot hips forward away from hands. Hold stretch.

exercise.name: PNF Seated Front Deltoid Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Continue to raise participant's arms upward behind their body, out to sides. Hold stretch.

exercise.name: Wall Front Deltoid Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Bring rear end and back toward wall and squat down. Hold stretch for 20 seconds.

exercise.name: Barbell Upright Row
exercise.execution: Pull bar to neck with elbows leading. Allow wrists to flex as bar rises. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Wide Grip Upright Row
exercise.execution: Pull bar to neck with elbows leading. Allow wrists to flex as bar rises. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: With elbows slightly bent, raise arms to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable One Arm Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: With elbow slightly bent, raise arm to side away from low pulley until elbow is shoulder height. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Lateral Raise (pulleys close)
exercise.execution: With elbows slightly bent, raise arms to side until elbows are shoulder height. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Seated Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: With elbows slightly bent, raise arms to side until elbows are shoulder height. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Upright Row
exercise.execution: Pull bar to neck with elbows leading. Allow wrists to flex as bar rises. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Bar Upright Row
exercise.execution: Pull bar to neck with elbows leading. Allow wrists to flex as bar rises. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Upright Row (dual pulley)
exercise.execution: Pull handles up to front of shoulders with elbows leading and cables crossed. Allow wrists to flex as stirrups are lifted. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable One Arm Upright Row
exercise.execution: Pull stirup to front side of shoulder with elbow leading. Allow wrist to flex as stirrup is lifted. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Upright Row (with rope attachment)
exercise.execution: Pull rope ends to front of shoulders with elbows leading. Allow wrists to flex as stirrups are lifted. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Upright Row (stirrup attachments)
exercise.execution: Pull handles to front of shoulders with elbows leading. Allow wrists to flex as stirrups are lifted. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Wide Grip Upright Row
exercise.execution: Pull bar to neck with elbows leading. Allow wrists to flex as bar rises. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Y Raise
exercise.execution: With elbows slightly bent, raise arms upward and outward to sides in Y configuration until elbows are approximately lateral to each ear. Lower stirrups forward and downward in reverse pattern. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Seated Y Raise
exercise.execution: Raise arms upward and outward to sides in Y configuration while allowing elbows to partially bend. Pull back until elbows are approximately lateral to each ear. Lower stirrups forward and downward until arms are extended straight in front of body. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Seated Y Raise (with rope attachment)
exercise.execution: With torso upright pull rope upward over head until elbows are approximately lateral to each ear. Lower stirrups forward and downward until arms are extended straight in front of body. Repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Incline Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Raise dumbbell from until upper arm is perpendicular to torso. Maintain slight fixed bend in elbow throughout exercise. Lower dumbbell to front of upper leg and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Incline Y Raise
exercise.execution: With elbows slightly bent, raise arms with dumbbells upward and outward to sides in Y configuration until elbows are approximately lateral to each ear. Lower dumbbells in reverse pattern until they are below shoulders and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Raise upper arms to sides until slightly bent elbows are shoulder height while maintaining elbows' height above or equal to wrists. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell One Arm Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Raise upper arm to side until slightly bent elbow is shoulder height while maintaining elbow's height above or equal to wrist. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell One Arm Seated Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Raise upper arm to side until slightly bent elbow is shoulder height while maintaining elbow's height above or equal to wrist. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Seated Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Raise upper arms to sides until slightly bent elbows are shoulder height while maintaining elbows' height above or equal to wrists. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Lying Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Raise dumbbell from floor until arm is vertical. Maintain fixed elbow position (10° to 30° angle) throughout exercise. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Raise
exercise.execution: Pull dumbbells up to sides of ribs with elbows out to sides. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Upright Row
exercise.execution: Pull dumbbells to front of shoulder with elbows leading out to sides. Allow wrists to flex as dumbbells rise upward. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell One Arm Upright Row
exercise.execution: Pull dumbbell to front of shoulder with elbow leading. Allow wrist to flex as dumbbell rises upward. Lower and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Seated Upright Row
exercise.execution: Pull dumbbell to front of shoulder with elbow leading out to side. Allow wrists to flex as dumbbell rises upward. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Barbell Upright Row (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Pull bar to neck with elbows leading. Allow wrists to flex as bar rises. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Lateral Raise (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Raise arms to sides until upper arms are horizontal. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Raise arms to sides until upper arms are horizontal. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Extended Arm Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Raise lever handles to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Maintain elbows' height above or equal to wrists. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Extended Arm Kneeling Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Raise lever handles to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Maintain elbows' height above or equal to wrists. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Raise arms to sides until upper arms are horizontal. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Upright Row
exercise.execution: Pull bar to neck with elbows leading. Allow wrists to flex as bar rises. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Fixed Bar Side Deltoid Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Turn body into upper arm. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Side Deltoid Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Push elbow toward chest. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Suspended Y Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Raise arms upward and outward in shape of a Y while keeping arms straight. Return and lower body back in opposite motion until arms are extended straight forward in original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Angled Side Bridge
exercise.execution: Raise hips upward by lateral flexion of spine. Lower to original position and repeat. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Barbell Rear Delt Raise
exercise.execution: Pull barbell behind hips and low back up as far as possible allowing elbows to travel up behind body to each side. Flex wrists near top of movement so bar can be raised higher. Lower until arms and wrists are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Rear Delt Row
exercise.execution: Keeping upper arm perpendicular to torso, pull barbell up toward upper chest until upper arms are just beyond horizontal. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Lying Rear Delt Row
exercise.execution: Keeping upper arm perpendicular to torso, pull barbell up toward upper chest until upper arms are just beyond parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Reverse Fly
exercise.execution: Pull stirrups out to sides, maintaining stiff elbow position throughout exercise. Return to original position and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Seated Reverse Fly
exercise.execution: Keeping elbows pointed high, pull stirrups out to sides, maintaining slightly bent elbow position throughout exercise. Return to original position and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable One Arm Reverse Fly
exercise.execution: Keeping elbows pointed high, pull stirrup out to side, maintaining fixed elbow position throughout exercise. Return to original position and repeat. Repeat with other arm.

exercise.name: Cable Supine Reverse Fly
exercise.execution: Pull upper arms down to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Maintain upper arms perpendicular to torso and fixed elbow position (just slightly bent) as arms are pulled down to sides. Return arms to original position and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Rear Delt Row
exercise.execution: Pull cable attachment toward upper chest, just below neck, with elbows up out to sides until elbows travel slightly behind back. Keep upper arms horizontal, perpendicular to trunk. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable One Arm Rear Delt Row
Cable Standing Rear Delt Row (with rope)
Cable Rear Delt Row (stirrups)
exercise.execution: Pull stirrups out to sides, keeping elbows at shoulder height until elbows travel slightly behind back. Allow wrists to follow elbows. Keep upper arms horizontal, perpendicular to trunk. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Seated Rear Delt Row (stirrups)
exercise.execution: Pull stirrups out to sides, keeping elbows at shoulder height until elbows travel slightly behind back. Allow wrists to follow elbows. Keep upper arms horizontal, perpendicular to trunk. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Standing Rear Delt Row (stirrups)
exercise.execution: Pull stirrups out to sides, keeping elbows at shoulder height until elbows travel slightly behind back. Allow wrists to follow elbows. Keep upper arms horizontal, perpendicular to trunk. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Rear Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Raise upper arms to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Maintain upper arms perpendicular to torso and slight bend in elbows as arms are raised to sides. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable One Arm Rear Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Raise arm to side until elbow is shoulder height. Maintain upper arm perpendicular to torso and fixed elbow position (10° to 30° angle) throughout exercise. Lower and repeat. Repeat with other arm.

exercise.name: Cable Seated Rear Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Pull stirrups out to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Maintain upper arms perpendicular to torso and fixed elbow position (10° to 30° angle) throughout exercise. Lower until arms contact sides of legs. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Standing Cross Row
exercise.execution: Pull both cable attachments by moving elbows back to sides. Keep upper arms horizontal, perpendicular to trunk. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable One Arm Standing Cross Row
exercise.execution: Pull stirrup back with elbow up at shoulder height until elbow travels just behind shoulder. Keep upper arm horizontal, perpendicular to trunk. Return until arm is fully extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Lying Rear Delt Row
exercise.execution: Keeping upper arm perpendicular to torso and dumbbells just below elbows, pull dumbbells up until elbows are just above shoulders. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Incline Rear Delt Row
exercise.execution: Keeping upper arm perpendicular to torso and dumbbells just below elbows, pull dumbbells up until elbows are just above shoulders. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Lying Rear Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Raise upper arms to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Maintain upper arms perpendicular to torso and fixed elbow position (10° to 30° angle) throughout exercise. Maintain height of elbows above wrists by raising "pinkie" side up. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Lying One Arm Rear Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Raise upper arm to side until elbow is shoulder height. Maintain upper arms perpendicular to torso with elbow straight throughout exercise. Maintain palm forward position. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Rear Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Raise upper arms to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Maintain upper arms perpendicular to torso and fixed elbow position (10° to 30° angle) throughout exercise. Maintain height of elbows above wrists by raising "pinkie finger" side up. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Rear Delt Row
exercise.execution: Pull dumbbell up out to side with upper arm perpendicular to trunk until upper arm is just beyond horizontal. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Seated Rear Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Raise upper arms to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Maintain upper arms perpendicular to torso and fixed elbow position (10° to 30° angle) throughout exercise. Maintain elbows height above wrists by raising "pinkie finger" side up. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Side Lying Rear Delt Raise
exercise.execution: Raise dumbbell from floor until it travels above shoulder. Return dumbbell to floor at original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Incline Rear Delt Row (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Pull lever with elbows forward out to sides until upper arms are just beyond parallel, keeping upper arm perpendicular to torso. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Lying Rear Lateral Raise (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Pull arms up until elbows are beyond back. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Rear Delt Raise (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Pull lever up as far as possible allowing elbows to travel up behind body to each side. Lower until arms are straight and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Rear Delt Row (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Pull lever with elbows up out to sides until upper arms are just beyond parallel, keeping upper arm horizontal, perpendicular to torso. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Rear Delt Row (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Pull lever with elbows up out to sides until upper arms are just beyond parallel, keeping upper arm horizontal, perpendicular to torso. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Rear Lateral Raise (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Pull lever handles out to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Maintain upper arms perpendicular to torso and fixed elbow position (10° to 30° angle) throughout exercise. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever T-Bar Rear Delt Row (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: With elbows out to sides, pull bar up toward upper chest until elbows are same height as shoulders or just beyond, keeping upper arm perpendicular to torso. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Lying Rear Lateral Raise
exercise.execution: Pull arms up until elbows are beyond back. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Rear Lateral Raise (on lateral raise machine)
exercise.execution: Maintaining torso position, raise upper arms to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Rear Lateral Raise (on extended arm kneeling lateral raise machine)
exercise.execution: Maintaining torso position, raise handles to sides until upper arm is shoulder height. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Rear Delt Row
exercise.execution: Pull lever with elbows up out to sides until upper arms are just beyond parallel, keeping upper arm horizontal, perpendicular to torso. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Reverse Fly (parallel grip)
exercise.execution: Keeping elbows pointed high, pull handles apart and to rear until elbows are just behind back. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Reverse Fly (gripless)
exercise.execution: Pull arms apart and back until elbows are slightly beyond back. Return to starting position and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Reverse Fly (on pec deck)
exercise.execution: Pull arms back until elbows are beyond back. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Reverse Fly (overhand grip)
exercise.execution: Keeping elbows pointed high, pull handles apart and to rear until elbows are just behind back Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Reverse Fly (pronated parallel grip)
exercise.execution: Keeping elbows pointed high, pull handles apart and to rear until elbows are just behind back. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Rear Delt Row
exercise.execution: Keeping upper arm perpendicular to torso, pull bar up toward upper chest until upper arms are just beyond parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Rear Delt Inverted Row
exercise.execution: Pull shoulders toward bar while keeping body straight, elbows to sides of shoulders, and upper arms perpendicular to torso, until upper arms are parallel to one another, or just beyond. Lower body while keeping elbows positioned high to sides of shoulders until arms are extended straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Rear Delt Inverted Row (high bar)
exercise.execution: Lower body while keeping body straight, elbows high, and upper arms perpendicular to torso, until arms are extended straight. Pull shoulders toward bar while keeping elbows up high until upper arms are parallel to one another, or just beyond. Repeat.

exercise.name: Rear Delt Inverted Row (on hips)
exercise.execution: Keeping hips on floor, low back straight, and elbow pointed out to sides; pull torso up to bar. Return when upper arms are just beyond parallel to one another. Lower body downward until arms are extended straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Rear Delt Row
exercise.execution: Pull body up while keeping elbows pointed directly out to each side and body and legs straight. Pull until elbows are directly lateral to each side without allowing elbows to drop. Return until arms are extended straight and shoulders are stretched forward, maintaining high elbow position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Reverse Fly

exercise.name: Cable Lying Fly

exercise.name: Cable Seated Fly

exercise.name: Cable Bench Press
exercise.execution: Push stirrups up over each shoulder until arms are straight and parallel to one another. Return stirrups to original position, until slight stretch is felt in shoulders or chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Bar Bench Press

exercise.name: Cable Chest Press

exercise.name: Cable Decline Chest Press

exercise.name: Cable Bar Standing Decline Chest Press

exercise.name: Cable Standing Decline Chest Press

exercise.name: Dumbbell Decline Fly

exercise.name: Side Lying Teres Minor Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Keeping elbow bend at a right angle, push forearm downward toward floor. Hold stretch. Repeat on opposite side.

exercise.name: Supine Infraspinatus Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Keeping elbows bend at a right angles, push forearms downward toward floor and hold stretch.

exercise.name: Prone Infraspinatus Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Lower bend arms toward floor and hold stretch.

exercise.name: Suspended Shoulder External Rotation
exercise.execution: Pull handles apart from each side, while keeping fixed elbow position and body and legs straight throughout movement. Raise forward so handles are to each side of body. Return back until handles come back together in front of body. Repeat.

exercise.name: Fixed Bar Back Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Bend over allowing hips to fall back. Slightly lean torso toward stretched arm. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Machine-assisted Chest Dip
exercise.execution: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Machine-assisted Chest Dip (kneeling)
exercise.execution: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Bench Press
exercise.execution: Lower weight to chest. Press bar upward until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Bench Press (power lift)
exercise.execution: Lower weight to lower chest. Press bar upward until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Board Press
exercise.execution: Lower weight toward lower chest on to board. Press bar upward until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Floor Press
exercise.execution: Lower weight to lower chest until the triceps are completely on the floor. Relax momentarily, then press bar upward until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Guillotine Bench Press
exercise.execution: Lower weight to neck to upper chest. Upper arms will be perpendicular to torso. Press bar until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Bench Press (with chains)
exercise.execution: Lower weight to chest. Press bar upward until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Decline Bench Press
exercise.execution: Lower weight to chest. Press bar until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Chest Dip
exercise.execution: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Decline Fly
exercise.execution: Bring cable stirrups together above upper abdomen in hugging motion; elbows in fixed position and shoulders internally rotated so elbows are to sides. Return to starting position until chest is slightly stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Lying Fly
exercise.execution: Bring cable attachments together in hugging motion with elbows in fixed position and shoulders internally rotated so elbows are to sides. Return to starting position until slight stretch. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Seated Fly
exercise.execution: Keeping elbows pointed high, bring cable attachments together in hugging motion with elbows in fixed position. Return to starting position until slight stretch. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Standing Fly
exercise.execution: Bring cable attachments together in hugging motion with elbows in fixed position. Keep shoulders internally rotated so elbows are pointed upward at top and out to sides at bottom. Return to starting position until chest muscles are stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Bench Press
exercise.execution: Push stirrups up over each shoulder until arms are straight and parallel to one another. Return stirrups to original position, until slight stretch is felt in shoulders or chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Bar Bench Press
exercise.execution: Press bar upward until arms are extended. Lower bar to chest or until slight stretch is felt in shoulders. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Chest Press
exercise.execution: Push stirrups out straight until arms are straight and parallel to one another. Return stirrups to original position, until slight stretch is felt in shoulders or chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable One Arm Chest Press
exercise.execution: Push stirrups out straight in front of shoulder until arm is straight. Return stirrups to original position until slight stretch is felt through shoulder or chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Standing Chest Press
exercise.execution: Push stirrups forward until arms are straight and parallel to one another. Return stirrups to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Bar Standing Chest Press
exercise.execution: Push cable bar forward until arms are straight. Return cable bar to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Twisting Chest Press
exercise.execution: Push stirrup out in front of upper chest while turning torso away from pulley. Return stirrup and torso back to original position allowing torso to rotate back until slight stretch is felt through chest, shoulder or waist. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Decline Chest Press
exercise.execution: Push stirrups forward and slightly downward until arms are straight and parallel to one another. Return stirrups to original position, until slight stretch is felt in shoulders or chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Bar Standing Decline Chest Press
exercise.execution: Push cable bar forward and downward until bar is about hip height and arms are straight. Return cable bar to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Standing Decline Chest Press
exercise.execution: Push stirrups at forward/downward angle until arms are straight and parallel to one another. Return stirrups to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Twisting Standing Chest Press
exercise.execution: Push stirrups away from body, horizontally until arm is straight and inline with cable. Return stirrups to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulder. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Bench Press
exercise.execution: Press dumbbells up with elbows to sides until arms are extended. Lower weight to sides of chest until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulder. Repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Decline Bench Press
exercise.execution: Press dumbbells up with elbows to sides until arms are extended. Lower weight to sides of chest until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulder. Repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Decline Fly
exercise.execution: Lower dumbbells to sides until chest muscles are stretched with elbows fixed. Bring dumbbells together in wide hugging motion until dumbbells are nearly together. Repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Fly
exercise.execution: Lower dumbbells to sides until chest muscles are stretched with elbows fixed in slightly bent position. Bring dumbbells together in wide hugging motion until dumbbells are nearly together. Repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Pullover
exercise.execution: Keeping elbows slightly bent throughout movement, lower dumbbell over and beyond head until upper arms are in-line with torso. Pull dumbbell up and over chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Pullover (on apparatus)
exercise.execution: Keeping elbows slightly bent throughout movement, lower dumbbell over and beyond head until upper arms are in-line with torso. Pull dumbbell up and over chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Pullover (on arched bench)
exercise.execution: Keeping elbows slightly bent throughout movement, lower dumbbell over and beyond head until upper arms are in-line with torso. Pull dumbbell up and over chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Bench Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Press bar until arms are extended. Lower weight to upper chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Barbell Bench Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Lower weight to chest. Press bar until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Chest Dip (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Push lever down with elbows away from body. Return until chest is slightly stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Chest Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Press levers until arms are extended. Return weight until chest muscles are slightly stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Decline Chest Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until chest muscles are slightly stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Decline Chest Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until chest muscles are slightly stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Wide Grip Chest Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until chest muscles are slightly stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Chest Dip
exercise.execution: Push lever down by straightening arms. Return lever up with elbows flaring out until chest is slightly stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Chest Dip
exercise.execution: Push lever down by straightening arms. Return lever up with elbows flaring out until chest is slightly stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Bent-over Fly (on iron cross machine)
exercise.execution: Bring lever handles together in hugging motion with elbows in fixed position. Keep shoulders internally rotated so elbows are pointed upward at top and out to sides at bottom. Return to starting position until chest muscles are stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Decline Fly (gripless)
exercise.execution: Bring padded levers together by pushing pads forward and downward in hugging motion. Return to starting position until chests muscle are stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Lying Fly
exercise.execution: Bring padded levers upward and together in hugging motion. Return to starting position until chest muscles are stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Pec Deck Fly
exercise.execution: Push levers together. Return until chest muscles are stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Decline Pec Deck Fly
exercise.execution: Push levers together. Return until chest muscles are stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Fly
exercise.execution: Keeping elbows pointed high, push lever handles forward and together. Return to back toward original position until mild stretch is felt in chest or shoulder. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Fly
exercise.execution: Keeping elbows pointed high, push lever handles forward and together. Return to back toward original position until mild stretch is felt in chest or shoulder. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Fly (gripless)
exercise.execution: Bring padded levers forward and together in hugging motion. Return to starting position until stretch in chests or shoulder is felt. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Iron Cross Fly
exercise.execution: Push levers downward and together in hugging motion. Keep shoulders internally rotated so elbows are pointed slightly upward at top and out to sides at bottom. Return to starting position until chest muscles are stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Bench Press
exercise.execution: Press bar until arms are extended. Lower weight to upp er chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Chest Press
exercise.execution: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until chest muscles are slightly stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Alternating Chest Press
exercise.execution: Press one lever until arm is extended. Return lever back until chest muscle is slightly stretched. Repeat with opposite arm, alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Lever Chest Press
exercise.execution: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until chest muscles are slightly stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Parallel Grip Chest Press
exercise.execution: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until shoulders or chest feels slightly stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Decline Chest Press
exercise.execution: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until chest muscles are slightly stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Alternating Decline Chest Press
exercise.execution: Press one lever until arm is extended. Return lever back until chest muscle is slightly stretched. Repeat with opposite arm, alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Lever Decline Bench Press
exercise.execution: Press bar until arms are extended. Lower weight to chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Standing Chest Dip
exercise.execution: Push lever down by straightening arms. Return lever up with elbows flaring out until chest is slightly stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Horizontal Grip Standing Chest Dip
exercise.execution: Push lever down by straightening arms. Return lever up with elbows flaring out until chest is slightly stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Bench Press
exercise.execution: Lower weight to chest. Press bar until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Decline Bench Press
exercise.execution: Lower weight to chest. Press bar until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Chest Dip
exercise.execution: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Push-up
exercise.execution: Keeping body straight, lower body to floor by bending arms. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Push-up (on handles)
exercise.execution: Keeping body ridged, lower body downward by bending arms until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Push body back up until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Band-assisted Chest Dip
exercise.execution: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Chest Dip
exercise.execution: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Chest Dip (between benches)
exercise.execution: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Chest Dip (bent knees between benches)
exercise.execution: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Push-up
exercise.execution: Keeping body straight, lower body to floor by bending arms. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Incline Push-up
exercise.execution: Keeping body straight, lower chest to edge of box or platform by bending arms. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Incline Push-up (on bar)
exercise.execution: Keeping body straight, lower chest to bar by bending arms. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Push-up (on knees)
exercise.execution: Keeping body straight and knees bent, lower body to floor by bending arms. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Self-assisted Chest Dip
exercise.execution: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. If necessary, use minimal assistance of lower body to control descent, allowing knees and hips to bend, keeping forefeet in contact with bench or elevation. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight and repeat, again with minimal assistance from legs.

exercise.name: Suspended Chest Dip
exercise.execution: Push body up until arms are straight. Lower body until slight stretch is felt in shoulders. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Self-assisted Chest Dip
exercise.execution: Lower body by bending arms back. If necessary, use minimal assistance of lower body to control descent, allowing knees to bend, keeping feet in contact with floor. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up back up until arms are straight. Repeat with minimal assistance from legs.

exercise.name: Suspended Chest Press
exercise.execution: Lower body by bending arms while keeping body straight. Allow handles to come apart slightly to keep in-line with elbows flaring out. Stop descent once mild stretch is felt through shoulders or chest. Push body up to original position, allowing handles to travel inward to keep in line with elbows converging until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Fly
exercise.execution: Lower body by allowing suspension handles to separate outward until mild stretch is felt in chest. Reverse motion by bringing handles back together in hugging motion. Repeat.

exercise.name: Behind Head Chest Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Pull elbows back further behind ears. Hold stretch.

exercise.name: PNF Behind Head Chest Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Pull participant's elbows back while stabilizing participant's torso with leg. Hold stretch.

exercise.name: Doorway Chest Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Turn body away from positioned arm. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Lying Chest Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Roll body onto side of bent arm by pushing onto floor with opposite arm and positioning bent upper leg over straight lower leg until stretch is felt. Hold stretch. Repeat in opposite position.

exercise.name: Straight Arm Chest Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Turn body away from positioned arm. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Doorway Modified Chest Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Lean into wall allowing shoulder to be pushed back. Turn body away from positioned arm. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Barbell Incline Bench Press
exercise.execution: Lower weight to upper chest. Press bar until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Incline Bench Press
exercise.execution: Push stirrups up over each shoulder until arms are straight and parallel to one another. Return stirrups to original position, until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Bar Incline Bench Press
exercise.execution: Press bar upward until arms are extended. Lower bar to upper chest or until slight stretch is felt in shoulders. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Incline Chest Press
exercise.execution: Push stirrups away from body, slightly upward at 30º to 45º until arms are straight and parallel to one another. Return stirrups to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Standing Incline Chest Press
exercise.execution: Push stirrups forward and upward at 30º to 45º angle until arms are straight and parallel to one another. Return stirrups to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Bar Standing Incline Chest Press
exercise.execution: Push cable bar forward and upward at 30º to 45º until arms are straight. Return cable bar to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable One Arm Standing Incline Chest Press
exercise.execution: Push stirrups forward and upward at 30º to 45º until arm is straight and in-line with cable. Return stirrup to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulder. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Cable Incline Fly
exercise.execution: Lower stirrups outward to sides of shoulders. Keep elbows fixed in slightly bent position. When a stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, bring stirrups back together in hugging motion above upper chest until stirrups are nearly together Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Standing Incline Fly
exercise.execution: Keeping elbows fixed in slightly bent position, bring stirrups together in upwardly arching, hugging motion, at 30º to 45º angle until they meet at top of motion. Lower stirrups to original position in reverse pattern. As soon as stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, repeat motion.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Incline Bench Press
exercise.execution: Press dumbbells up with elbows to sides until arms are extended. Lower weight to sides of upper chest until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulder. Repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Incline Fly
exercise.execution: Lower dumbbells outward to sides of shoulders. Keep elbows fixed in slightly bent position. When a stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, bring dumbbells back together in hugging motion above upper chest until dumbbells are nearly together. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Incline Bench Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Press lever bars up until arms are extended. Lower weight toward upper chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Barbell Incline Bench Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Lower weight to chest. Press bar until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Parallel Grip Incline Bench Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Press lever bars up until arms are extended. Lower weight toward upper chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Incline Chest Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until chest muscles are slightly stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Incline Chest Press (on Hammer military press)
exercise.execution: Press levers until arms are extended. Return weight until chest muscles are slightly stretched with elbows positioned out to sides. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Incline Bench Press
exercise.execution: Press bar until arms are extended. Lower weight to upper chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Parallel Grip Incline Bench Press
exercise.execution: Press lever bars up until arms are extended. Lower weight toward upper chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Incline Chest Press
exercise.execution: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until shoulders or chest feels slightly stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Alternating Incline Chest Press
exercise.execution: Press one lever until arm is extended. Return lever back down until chest muscle is slightly stretched. Repeat with opposite arm, alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Lever Parallel Grip Incline Chest Press
exercise.execution: Press lever bars up until arms are extended. Return weight until shoulders or chest feels slightly stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Incline Fly
exercise.execution: Raise lever upward and together in hugging motion. Lower weight until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulder. Repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Incline Bench Press
exercise.execution: Lower weight to upper chest. Press bar until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Decline Push-up
exercise.execution: Keeping body straight, lower upper body to floor by bending arms. To allow for full descent, pull head back slightly without arching back. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Decline Push-up (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Keeping hips straight, lower upper body to floor by bending arms. To allow for full descent, pull head back slightly without arching back. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Pike Push-up
exercise.execution: Lower head between ends of benches by bending arms. Push body back up to original position by extending arms. Repeat.

exercise.name: Doorway Chest Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Turn body away from positioned arm. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Machine-assisted Chest Dip
exercise.execution: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Standing Fly
exercise.execution: Bring cable attachments together in hugging motion with elbows in fixed position. Keep shoulders internally rotated so elbows are pointed upward at top and out to sides at bottom. Return to starting position until chest muscles are stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Chest Dip
exercise.execution: Push lever down by straightening arms. Return lever up with elbows flaring out until chest is slightly stretched. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Chest Dip
exercise.execution: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Bench Angel
exercise.mechanic: Slowly move arms apart, out to each side, while pushing shoulders down into bench and keeping arms as low as possible. Continue pulling arms toward body until hands are out to sides of hips without allowing shoulders to raise up off bench. Slowly return arms to starting position while keeping shoulder pushed down against bench. Repeat.

exercise.name: Doorway Modified Chest Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Lean into wall allowing shoulder to be pushed back. Turn body away from positioned arm. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Lying Shoulder Girdle Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Push shoulders, forearms, and back of hand into floor or mat and slowly move arms toward sides of head. Still pushing shoulders and back of arms into floor, slowly arms toward sides.

exercise.name: Towel Shoulder Girdle Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Pull towel back away from back of head while attempting to pull towel outward on each side.

exercise.name: Wall Angel
exercise.mechanic: Push shoulders and back of arms and hands into wall and slowly raise arms as high as possible. Still pushing shoulders arms, slowly lower arms to starting position.

exercise.name: Doorway Chest Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Turn body away from positioned arm. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Broom Stick Subscapularis Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Pull lower end of pole forward and upward so shoulder is externally rotated. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Barbell Incline Shoulder Raise
exercise.execution: Raise shoulders toward bar as high as possible. Lower shoulders to bench and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Incline Shoulder Raise
exercise.execution: Raise shoulders toward stirrups as high as possible. Lower shoulders down and back and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable One Arm Incline Push
exercise.execution: Push stirrup forward and up at 30º to 45º while rotating torso away allowing shoulder to be extended forward. Return stirrups to original position, until slight stretch, and repeat. Continue with opposite side.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Incline Shoulder Raise
exercise.execution: Raise shoulders toward dumbbells as high as possible. Lower shoulders to bench and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Incline Shoulder Raise (plate loaded)

exercise.name: Smith Incline Shoulder Raise

exercise.execution: Push stirrups forward and upward at 30º to 45º until arm is straight and in-line with cable. Return stirrup to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulder. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Cable Twisting Chest Press
exercise.execution: Push stirrup out in front of upper chest while turning torso away from pulley. Return stirrup and torso back to original position allowing torso to rotate back until slight stretch is felt through chest, shoulder or waist. Repeat.

exercise.name: Push-up Plus
exercise.execution: Keeping body straight, lower body to floor by bending arms. Push body up until arms are extended. Continue lifting body further up by pushing shoulders infront of chest. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Push Crunch
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso from bench, keeping low back on bench. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Push Sit-up
exercise.execution: Raise torso from bench as high as possible by bending waist and hips. Keep weight positioned above shoulders. Achieve near upright posture (hip flexibility, incline, and initial hip position permitting). Return to original lying posture with back of shoulders contacting padded incline board. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Lying Crunch (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: With hips stationary, flex waist so elbows travel toward thighs. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Lying Leg-Hip Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips while flexing knees until hips are fully flexed. Raise hips from floor by flexing waist. Return until waist, hips and knees are extended downward. Repeat.

exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips while flexing knees until hips are fully flexed. Raise hips from floor by flexing waist. Return until legs are extended horizontally. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Lying Straight Leg-Hip Raise

exercise.name: Cable Seated Crunch

exercise.name: Cable Overhead Seated Crunch

exercise.name: Cable Seated Crunch (plate loaded)

exercise.name: Cable Standing Overhead Crunch

exercise.name: Cable Standing Overhead Crunch (multi-exercise bar)

exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso from bench, keeping low back on bench. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline bench. Repeat.

Achieve near upright posture (hip flexibility, incline, and initial hip position permitting). Return to original lying posture with back of shoulders, contacting padded incline board. Repeat.

exercise.execution: With hips stationary, raise upper back pad by flexing waist. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Lying Leg Raise Crunch (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Pull handles toward legs while pulling lower leg bar toward arms by flexing waist and hips. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Leg Raise Crunch (plate loaded)

exercise.name: Lever Vertical Leg-Hip Raise (plate loaded)

exercise.name: Lever Lying Crunch
exercise.execution: With hips stationary, raise upper back pad by flexing waist. Return and repeat.

exercise.execution: Pull lower leg bar up by flexing hips toward arms by flexing hips then waist. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist, raising hips from board. Return until waist and hips are extended down to original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Push Crunch
exercise.execution: Push resistance lever forward by flexing waist. Return by allowing upper body to be pushed back until low back is hyperextended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Leg Raise Crunch

exercise.name: Lever Side Lying Leg Hip Raise
exercise.execution: Pull knees toward arms by flexing waist and hips. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Leg Hip Raise (ab coaster)
exercise.execution: Slide forward and up by pulling knees up high. Deliberately attempt to flex waist in a "C" shape. Return sled down and back arching spine in opposite direction while keeping hips bent. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Crunch
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso from bench. Keep low back on bench and raise torso up as high as possible. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Crunch (plate on chest)
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso from mat. Keep low back on mat and raise torso up as high as possible. Return until back of shoulders contact mat. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Crunch (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso. Return to original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Overhead Crunch (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Keeping arms extended and medicine ball over upper chest, flex waist to raise upper torso. Return to original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Incline Crunch
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso from bench. Keep low back on bench and raise torso up as high as possible. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Incline Crunch (arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso from bench. Keep low back on bench and raise torso up as high as possible. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Incline Sit-up
exercise.execution: Raise torso from bench by bending waist and hips. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Incline Sit-up (arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Raise torso from bench by bending waist and hips. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat.

exercise.name: Medicine Ball Overhead Throw Sit-up (machine)
exercise.execution: With ball in both hands, lie down onto back support while lowering medicine ball behind head. Raise torso from back support by bending waist and hips while raising ball overhead. Immediately throw ball into target and grasp other medicine ball at bottom of chute. Repeat movement.

exercise.name: Medicine Ball Chest Throw Sit-up (machine)
exercise.execution: With ball in both hands, lie down onto back support while lowering medicine ball to chest. Raise torso from back support by bending waist and hips while pushing ball away from chest. Immediately throw ball into target and grasp other medicine ball at bottom of chute. Repeat movement.

exercise.name: Weighted Sit-up
exercise.execution: Raise torso from floor by bending waist and hips. Return until back of shoulders contact with floor or mat. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Sit-up (arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Raise torso from floor by bending waist and hips. Return until back of shoulders contact with floor or mat. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Hanging Leg-Hip Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are fully flexed. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist. Return until waist, hips, and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Incline Leg-Hip Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips while flexing knees until hips are fully flexed. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist, raising hips from board. Return until waist, hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Lying Leg-Hip Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips while flexing knees until hips are fully flexed. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist, raising hips from board. Return until waist, hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Vertical Leg-Hip Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are fully flexed. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist, raising hips from back board. Return until waist, hips, and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Vertical Leg-Hip Raise (Bosu support)
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees. As hips approach full flexion, lean back. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist and raising hips and low back from convexed surface. Return until waist, hips, and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Vertical Leg-Hip Raise (on parallel bars)
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are fully flexed. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist. Return until waist, hips, and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted V-up
exercise.execution: While keeping feet together, simultaneously raise straight legs and torso. Reach toward raised feet. Return to starting position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Standing Twisting Crunch
exercise.execution: Flex and twist spine so torso pulls strap forward and downward while twisting one shoulder to forward center. Return until back of shoulders return to back pad. Repeat alternating twists with opposite sides.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Twisting Leg Raise Crunch (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Pull handles down while pulling lower leg bar up and over to one side by flexing and twisting waist and pelvis. Return and repeat movement to opposite side. Continue alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Weighted Incline Twisting Crunch (arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to raise upper torso from bench to one side. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

exercise.name: Weighted Side Crunch
exercise.execution: Flex waist, raising upper torso off surface. Return until back of shoulders return to surface. Repeat and continue with movement in opposite position.

exercise.name: Weighted Side Crunch (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso. Return to original position and repeat. Position legs in opposite position and continue.

exercise.name: Weighted Twisting Crunch
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to raise upper torso off surface to one side. Return until back of shoulders return to surface. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

exercise.name: Weighted Twisting Crunch (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso. Return to original position and repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Incline Twisting Sit-up
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat to opposite side, alternating twists.

exercise.name: Weighted Incline Twisting Sit-up (arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

exercise.name: Weighted Twisting Sit-up
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact floor or mat. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

exercise.name: Weighted Twisting Sit-up (arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact floor or mat. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

exercise.name: Barbell Turkish Get-up
exercise.execution: Stand up while keeping arms straight and vertical above shoulders.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Turkish Get-up
exercise.execution: Stand up while keeping arm with dumbbell straight and vertical. Assist by using free arm, pushing off into floor.

exercise.name: Crunch
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso from mat. Keep low back on mat and raise torso up as high as possible. Return until back of shoulders contact mat. Repeat.

exercise.name: Crunch (arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso from mat. Keep low back on mat and raise torso up as high as possible. Return until back of shoulders contact mat. Repeat.

exercise.name: Crunch (arms down)
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso from mat or bench. Keep low back on floor or mat and raise torso up as high as possible. Extend hands toward sides of heels. Return until back of shoulders contact mat or bench. Repeat.

exercise.name: Crunch Up
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso from floor. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat.

exercise.name: Incline Crunch
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso from bench. Keep low back on bench and raise torso up as high as possible. Return until back of shoulders contact incline board. Repeat.

exercise.name: Incline Crunch (arms down)
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso from bench. Keep low back on bench and raise torso up as high as possible. Return until back of shoulders contact incline board. Repeat.

exercise.name: Ball Crunch (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso. Return to original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Crunch (on stability ball, arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso. Return to original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Jack-knife Sit-up
exercise.execution: Simultaneously raise knees and torso until hips and knees are flexed. Return to starting position with waist, hips and knees extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Hanging Leg-Hip Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are fully flexed. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist. Return until waist, hips, and knees are extended downward. Repeat.

exercise.name: Hanging Leg-Hip Raise (with ab straps)
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are fully flexed. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist. Return until waist, hips, and knees are extended downward. Repeat.

exercise.name: Hanging Straight Leg-Hip Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips until fully flexed. Continue to raise feet toward bar by flexing waist. Return until waist and hips are extended downward. Repeat.

exercise.name: Incline Leg-Hip Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are fully flexed. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist, raising hips from board. Return until waist, hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lying Leg-Hip Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips while flexing knees until hips are fully flexed. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist, raising hips from board. Return until waist, hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Leg-Hip Raise (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are fully flexed. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist, raising hips from board. Return until waist, hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Vertical Leg-Hip Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are fully flexed. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist, raising hips from back board. Return until waist, hips, and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Vertical Leg-Hip Raise (parallel bars)
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are fully flexed. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist. Return until waist, hips, and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Vertical Straight Leg-Hip Raise (parallel bars)
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips until fully flexed. Continue to raise feet toward bar by flexing waist. Return until waist and hips are extended downward. Repeat.

exercise.name: Vertical Leg-Hip Raise (Bosu support)
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees. As hips approach full flexion, lean back. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist and raising hips and low back from convexed surface. Return until waist, hips, and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Incline Sit-up
exercise.execution: Raise torso from bench by bending waist and hips. Return until back of shoulders contact incline board. Repeat.

exercise.name: Incline Sit-up (arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Raise torso from bench by bending waist and hips. Raise crossed arms over knees at top. Return until back of shoulders contact incline board. Repeat.

exercise.name: Inverted Sit-up
exercise.execution: Raise trunk as high as possible by flexing hips and waist. Return to starting position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sit-up
exercise.execution: Raise torso from bench by bending waist and hips. Return until back of shoulders contact incline board. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sit-up (arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Raise torso from mat or bench by bending waist and hips. Raise crossed arms over knees at top. Return until back of shoulders contact mat or bench. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sit-up (arms down)
exercise.execution: Raise torso from mat or bench by bending waist and hips. Extend hands toward sides of heels. Return until back of shoulders contact mat or bench. Repeat.

exercise.name: V-up
