exercise.execution: Simultaneously raise straight legs and torso. Reach toward raised feet. Return to starting position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Jack-knife
exercise.execution: Pull legs under torso by bending hips and knees. Pull knees toward chest hips and knees until completely flexed. Return by extending hips and knees to original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Jack-knife Pike
exercise.execution: Pull knees toward shoulders while raising hips very high. Lower hips by extending body to original straight position, while keeping shins close to horizontal. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Pull Through
exercise.execution: Pull hips back while flexing spine in C shape. Raise hips up high by straightening spine and hips until straight.

exercise.name: Suspended Kneeling Rollout
exercise.execution: Lean body forward while maintaining small bend in hip. Allow arms to bend forward to sides of head. Bend over as far as possible. Raise body back up by pulling arms back until kneeling upright in original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Standing Rollout
exercise.execution: Lean body forward while extending hips and allowing arms to extend forward to sides of head. Bend over as far as possible. Raise body back up by pulling arms back until standing while being bent over slightly at hips in original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Hanging Leg Hip Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are fully flexed. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist. Return until waist, hips, and knees are extended downward. Repeat.

exercise.name: Front Plank
exercise.execution: Raise body upward by straightening body in straight line. Hold position.

exercise.name: Stability Ball Rollout
exercise.execution: Lean forward and roll ridged arms out over ball. Roll forward as far as possible. Raise body back up by pulling arms back until kneeling upright in original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Kneeling Abdominal Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Lean torso back by arching back. Hold stretch.

exercise.name: Lying (Prone) Abdominal Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Push torso up keeping pelvis on floor. Hold stretch.

exercise.name: Lying (supine) Abdominal Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Lift chest away from lower body while reach away with arms. Hold stretch.

exercise.name: Standing Abdominal Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Arch back by lift chest up and bringing arms back as far as possible. Hold stretch.

exercise.name: Abdominal Vacuum
exercise.execution: Pull navel into spine and hold.

exercise.name: Cable Kneeling Twisting Crunch
exercise.execution: With hips stationary, flex waist to one side so elbow travels toward mid-thigh on opposite side. Return to original position and repeat on opposite side. Continue by alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Cable Russian Twist (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Allow resistance from cable to turn torso downward, toward direction of pulley while keeping arms straight and perpendicular to torso throughout movement. Pull stirrup in an arch over shoulders by rotating torso to opposite direction of pulley until cable makes contact with shoulder. Return to original position in opposite direction and repeat. Continue with opposite side.

exercise.name: Cable Side Bend
exercise.execution: Pull stirrup by bending sideways through waist so torso moves away from pulley. Lower stirrup by leaning torso toward pulley. Repeat. Continue with opposite side.

exercise.name: Cable Side Crunch
exercise.execution: Pull stirrup downward by bending toward cable column through waist so torso moves toward base of cable column. Bend in opposite direction by leaning torso away from cable column, allowing stirrup to rise upward. Repeat. Continue with opposite side.

exercise.name: Cable Seated Twist
exercise.execution: Keeping arms straight, rotate torso to opposite side until cable makes contact with shoulder. Return to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite side.

exercise.name: Cable Seated Cross Arm Twist
exercise.execution: Rotate torso through waist to face opposite side until slight stretch if felt. Return to original side until slight stretch is felt. Repeat. Continue with opposite side.

exercise.name: Cable Standing Twisting Crunch
exercise.execution: Flex and twist spine so torso pulls strap forward and downward while twisting one shoulder to forward center. Return until back of shoulders return to back pad. Repeat alternating twists with opposite sides.

exercise.name: Cable Standing Twisting Crunch (single side)
exercise.execution: Flex and twist spine so shoulder pulls strap diagonally forward and downward away from pulley. Return until back of shoulder returns to back pad and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Twist
exercise.execution: Keeping arms straight, rotate torso to opposite side until cable makes contact with shoulder. Return to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite side.

exercise.name: Cable Twist (down up)
exercise.execution: Keeping arms straight, pull stirrup diagonally upward around shoulders by rotating torso and raising arms gradually upward until cable makes contact with side of body. Bend knees slightly more as stirrup approaches top. Return to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite side.

exercise.name: Cable Twist (up down)
exercise.execution: Keeping arms straight, pull stirrup diagonally downward around shoulders by rotating torso and gradually lowering arms downward until cable is just above shoulder. Gradually bend knees as stirrup makes its way around body and approaches bottom. Return to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite side.

exercise.name: Dumbbell 45° Side Bend
exercise.execution: Raise torso upward by lateral flexing waist. Lower torso by bending waist downward. Repeat. Position body facing opposite side and continue with opposite side.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Russian Twist (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Turn torso to one side while keeping arms straight and perpendicular to torso throughout movement. Return dumbbell back over shoulders by rotating torso to original position. Continue lowering dumbbell to opposite side. Repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Side Bend
exercise.execution: Bend waist to opposite side of dumbbell until slight stretch is felt. Lower to opposite side, same distance and repeat. Continue with opposite side.

exercise.name: Lever Barbell Side Bend (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Bend waist to opposite side of bar. Lower weight by bending toward side with bar and repeat. Continue with opposite side facing opposite direction.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Twisting Leg Raise Crunch (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Pull handles down while pulling lower leg bar up and over to one side by flexing and twisting waist and pelvis. Return and repeat movement to opposite side. Continue alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Side Leg Raise Crunch (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Pull handles down while pulling lower leg bar up by flexing waist and pelvis. Return and repeat. Turn seat to opposite side and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Kneeling Twist
exercise.execution: Rotate lower body through waist to opposite side. Return and repeat. Adjust range of motion setting to opposite side and repeat in opposite direction.

exercise.name: Lever Lying Twist
exercise.execution: Rotate torso through waist to opposite side. Return and repeat. Readjust range of motion setting to opposite side and repeat in opposite direction.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Side Bend
exercise.execution: With hips stationary, push down lever by bending to side so elbow points downward. Return and repeat. Position lower body to opposite side and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Twist
exercise.execution: Rotate torso through waist to opposite side. Return and repeat. Adjust range of motion setting to opposite side and repeat in opposite direction.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Twist
exercise.execution: Rotate torso through waist to opposite side. Return and repeat. Adjust range of motion setting to opposite side and repeat in opposite direction.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Twist
exercise.execution: Rotate torso through waist to opposite side. Return and repeat. Adjust range of motion setting to opposite side and repeat in opposite direction.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Twist (gripless)
exercise.execution: Rotate torso through waist to opposite side. Return and repeat. Adjust range of motion setting to opposite side and repeat in opposite direction.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Side Crunch
exercise.execution: With hips stationary, flex waist in "C" shape so elbows point downward. Return and repeat. Position lower body to opposite side and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Standing Side Bend
exercise.execution: Bend waist to opposite side of lever. Lower weight by bending to opposite side and repeat. Continue with opposite side facing opposite direction.

exercise.name: Sled Side Leg Hip Raise (ab coaster)
exercise.execution: Slide forward and up by pulling knees up high. Deliberately attempt to flex waist in a "C" shape. Return sled down and back arching spine in opposite direction while keeping hips bent. Repeat. Turn seat to opposite side and repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Lying Twist
exercise.execution: Lower legs to one side until side of thigh is on floor. Raise and lower legs to opposite side. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Bent-knee Lying Twist
exercise.execution: Lower legs to one side until side of thigh is on floor. Raise and lower legs to opposite side. Repeat.

exercise.name: Medicine Ball Straight Arm Russian Twist (legs extended)
exercise.execution: Turn torso to one side while keeping arms straight and perpendicular to torso throughout movement. Return weight back over shoulders by rotating torso to original position. Continue lowering weight to opposite side. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Russian Twist (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Turn torso to one side while keeping arms straight and perpendicular to torso throughout movement. Return weight back over shoulders by rotating torso to original position. Continue lowering weight to opposite side. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted 45° Side Bend
exercise.execution: Raise torso upward by lateral flexing waist. Lower torso by bending waist downward. Repeat. Position body facing opposite side and continue with opposite side.

exercise.name: Weighted Side Bend (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Raise side of torso up by laterally flexing waist. Lower torso back on ball and repeat. Position other side on ball and repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Weighted Incline Twisting Crunch (arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to raise upper torso from bench to one side. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

exercise.name: Weighted Side Crunch
exercise.execution: Flex waist, raising upper torso off surface. Return until back of shoulders return to surface. Repeat and continue with movement in opposite position.

exercise.name: Weighted Side Crunch (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso. Return to original position and repeat. Position legs in opposite position and continue.

exercise.name: Weighted Twisting Crunch
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to raise upper torso off surface to one side. Return until back of shoulders return to surface. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

exercise.name: Weighted Twisting Crunch (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso. Return to original position and repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Incline Twisting Sit-up
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat to opposite side, alternating twists.

exercise.name: Weighted Incline Twisting Sit-up (arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

exercise.name: Weighted Twisting Sit-up
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact floor or mat. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

exercise.name: Weighted Twisting Sit-up (arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact floor or mat. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

exercise.name: Cable Push Pull
exercise.execution: Pull low pulley stirrup back to side of ribcage while pushing high pulley stirrup forward until arm is extended, allowing torso to rotate to opposite side.

exercise.name: Cable Twisting Seated Row
exercise.execution: Pull cable attachment to side, extending and twisting through waist. Pull shoulders back and sit upright while pushing chest forward during contraction. Return until arm is extended and shoulder is stretched forward. Repeat and perform exercise with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Cable One Arm Seated High Row
exercise.execution: Pull cable attachment to side of torso, straightening back and leaning back slightly. Pull shoulder back and push chest forward during contraction. Return until arm is extended and torso is pulled forward. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Dumbbell One Arm Straight Leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: With knees straight, lower dumbbell between feet by bending hips and twisting waist, so shoulder of weighted side is turned forward. Allow hips to fall back and waist to bend as dumbbell approaches floor. Lift dumbbell upward and back to side by extending hips and waist until standing upright. Pull shoulder back if rounded. Repeat. Perform exercise with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Lever One Arm Jammer Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Push handles out and up while turning torso forward.

exercise.name: Lever Power Twist (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Move end of barbell upward, across, and downward to opposite side while shifting stance to opposite orientation by pivoting on forefeet and planting new forward foot.

exercise.name: Lever Push Pull (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Pull forward lever back while pushing other lever forward.

exercise.name: Angled Side Bridge
exercise.execution: Raise hips upward by lateral flexion of spine. Lower to original position and repeat. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Lying Twist
exercise.execution: Lower legs to one side until side of thigh is on floor. Raise and lower legs to opposite side. Repeat.

exercise.name: Bent-knee Lying Twist
exercise.execution: Lower legs to one side until side of thigh is on floor. Raise and lower legs to opposite side. Repeat.

exercise.name: Plank Twist (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Rotate hips so thighs roll over top of ball to one side. Rotate to opposite side and repeat.

exercise.name: Side Bend (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Raise side of torso up by lateral flexing waist. Lower torso back on ball and repeat. Position other side on ball and repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Side Bridge
exercise.execution: Raise hips upward by lateral flexion of spine. Lower to original position and repeat. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Bent Knee Side Bridge
exercise.execution: Raise hips upward by lateral flexion of spine. Lower to original position and repeat. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Hanging Twisting Leg Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs to one side by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed or knees are well above hips. Return until hips and knees are extended downward. Raise legs to opposite side in same manner. Continue by bending and lifting legs, alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Vertical Twisting Leg Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs to one side by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed or knees are above hips. Return until hips and knees are extended downward. Raise legs to opposite side in same manner. Continue by bending and lifting legs, alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Vertical Twisting Leg Raise (on dip bar)
exercise.execution: Raise legs to one side by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed or knees are above hips. Return until hips and knees are extended downward. Raise legs to opposite side in same manner. Continue by bending and lifting legs, alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Incline Twisting Sit-up
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

exercise.name: Incline Twisting Sit-up (arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Raise crossed arm over opposite knees at top. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

exercise.name: Twisting Sit-up
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact floor or mat. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

exercise.name: Twisting Sit-up (arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact floor or mat. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

exercise.name: Incline Twisting Crunch
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to raise upper torso from bench to one side. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

exercise.name: Incline Twisting Crunch (arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to raise upper torso from bench to one side. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

exercise.name: Side Crunch
exercise.execution: Flex waist, raising upper torso off mat or floor. Return until back of shoulders return to mat or floor. Repeat and continue with movement in opposite position.

exercise.name: Side Crunch (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso. Return to original position and repeat. Position legs in opposite position and continue.

exercise.name: Twisting Crunch
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to raise upper torso from mat to one side. Return until back of shoulders contact mat. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

exercise.name: Twisting Crunch (arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Flex and twist waist to raise upper torso from mat to one side. Return until back of shoulders contact mat. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

exercise.name: Twisting Crunch (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Flex waist to raise upper torso. Return to original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Hanging Windshield Wiper
exercise.execution: Turn legs to one side by rotating waist until stretch is felt through waist. Rotate legs to opposite side in same manner. Continue by rotating from side to side.

exercise.name: Suspended Pendulum
exercise.execution: Move both legs to one side then to opposite side by moving through waist and hips. Continue swinging legs side to side.

exercise.name: Suspended Side Bend
exercise.execution: Lower hips away from direction of suspension trainer anchor by laterally flexing spine. Return to original upright position and repeat. Reposition body facing opposite direction. Continue with other side.

exercise.name: Suspended Side Bridge
exercise.execution: Raise hips upward by lateral flexion of spine. Lower to original position and repeat. Reposition to opposite side and continue.

exercise.name: Suspended Twist
exercise.execution: While keeping arms straight and shoulders fixed, rotate torso up to one side. Twist until upright or slight stretch is felt in waist, whichever comes soonest. Rotate back to starting position and repeat. Continue on opposite side.

exercise.name: Suspended Twisting Jack-knife
exercise.execution: Pull knees toward one elbow by bending hips a nd knees to one side. Twist legs to one side, until hips and knees are completely flexed. Return by extending hips and knees to original straight position. Perform movement to opposite side. Continue by alternating each side.

exercise.name: Side Plank
exercise.execution: Raise body upward by straightening waist so body is ridged. Hold position. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Bent Knee Side Plank
exercise.execution: Raise body upward by straightening waist so hips and waist are ridged. Hold position. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Lying Bent Leg Oblique Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Bring both knees and hip to one side. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Lying Crossover Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Lower leg to opposite side toward hand. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Pretzel Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Turn torso further around by pushing side of knee with elbow. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Seated Bent Leg Oblique Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Bring both knees and hip to one side. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Barbell Hyperextension
exercise.execution: Raise upper body until hips and waist are fully extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is vertical. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Back Extension (on hyperextension apparatus)
exercise.execution: Lower body by bending waist until fully flexed. Raise or extend waist until torso is parallel to legs. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell 45° Hyperextension
exercise.execution: Raise upper body until hips and waist are fully extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is approximately perpendicular to legs. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell 45° Back Extension (on hyperextension apparatus)
exercise.execution: Lower body by bending waist until fully flexed. Raise, or extend waist until torso is parallel to legs. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Bent Knee Good-morning
exercise.execution: Bend hips to lower torso forward until parallel to floor. Bend knees slightly during descent. Raise torso until hips are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Deadlift
exercise.execution: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Block Pull
exercise.execution: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Deficit Deadlift
exercise.execution: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return weights to floor by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Rack Pull
exercise.execution: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Sumo Deadlift
exercise.execution: Pull bar up by driving feet outward while pulling chest up. Extend knees when bar passes knees. At top of lift, when torso is upright, drive shoulders back and chest up. Return weight to floor by bending hips back and knees pointed outward, while keeping chest high and back straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Sumo Block Pull
exercise.execution: Pull bar up by driving feet outward while pulling chest up. Extend knees when bar passes knees. At top of lift, when torso is upright, drive shoulders back and chest up. Return weight to blocks by bending hips back and knees pointed outward, while keeping chest high and back straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Stiff Leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: Lower bar to top of feet by bending hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight, flexing only slightly at bottom. With knees bent, lift bar by extending at hips until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Extend knees at top if desired. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Straight Leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: With knees straight, lower bar toward top of feet by bending hips and waist. Lift bar by extending waist and hip until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

exercise.name: Trap Bar Deadlift
exercise.execution: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Trap Bar Stiff Leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: Lower bar by bending hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight, flexing only slightly at bottom. With knees bent, lift bar by extending at hips until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Extend knees at top if desired. Repeat.

exercise.name: Trap Bar Straight Leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: With knees straight, lower bar down by bending hips. After hips can no longer flex, bend waist as weights approach floor. Hands should be lowered near sides of ankles. Set weight on floor. Lift bar by extending waist and hip until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Stiff Leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: Bow forward by bending hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight, flexing low back at bottom. With knees slightly bent, raise torso by extending at waist, then hips, gradually extending knees until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Straight Leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: With knees straight, bow forward by bending hips. Bend waist as stirrups approach lowest position. Lift dumbbells by extending hips and waist until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Straight Leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: With knees straight, lower dumbbells to top or sides of feet by bending hips. Allow hips to fall back and bend waist as dumbbell approaches feet. Lift dumbbells by extending hips and waist until standing upright. Pull shoulders back if rounded. Repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell One Arm Straight Leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: With knees straight, lower dumbbell between feet by bending hips and twisting waist, so shoulder of weighted side is turned forward. Allow hips to fall back and waist to bend as dumbbell approaches floor. Lift dumbbell upward and back to side by extending hips and waist until standing upright. Pull shoulder back if rounded. Repeat. Perform exercise with opposite arm.

exercise.name: Lever Deadlift (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Lift lever by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Stiff Leg Deadlift (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Bow forward by bending hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight, flexing low back at bottom. With knees slightly bent, raise torso by extending at waist, then hips, gradually extending knees until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Straight Leg Deadlift (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: With knees straight, bow forward by bending hips. Bend waist as stirrups approach lowest position. Lift lever by extending hips and waist until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Back Extension
exercise.execution: Extend spine until hyperextended. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Back Extension
exercise.execution: Extend spine until hyperextended. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Back Extension
exercise.execution: Extend spine until hyperextended. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Kneeling Back Extension
exercise.execution: Extend spine until hyperextended. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Pull Back Extension
exercise.execution: Pull lever back until spine hyperextends while keeping hips pushed back against pad. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Bent Knee Good-morning
exercise.execution: Bend hips to lower torso forward until parallel to floor. Bend knees slightly during descent. Raise torso until hips are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Deadlift
exercise.execution: Squat down to lower bar by bending hips and knees. Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Stiff Leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: With knees slightly bent, Lower bar toward top of feet by bending hips. Keep waist straight, flexing only slightly at bottom. Lift bar by extending at hips until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Extend knees at top if desired. Repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Straight Leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: With knees straight, lower bar toward top of feet by bending hips. After hips can no longer flex, bend waist as bar approaches top of feet. Lift bar by extending waist and hip until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Hyperextension
exercise.execution: Raise upper body until hips and waist are fully extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is vertical. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Back Extension (on hyperextension apparatus)
exercise.execution: Lower body by bending waist until fully flexed. Raise, or extend waist until torso is parallel to legs. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Back Extension (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Raise torso off of ball by hyperextending spine. Lower torso onto ball allowing spine to flex. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted 45° Hyperextension
exercise.execution: Raise upper body until hips and waist are fully extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is approximately perpendicular to legs. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted 45° Back Extension (on hyperextension apparatus)
exercise.execution: Lower body by bending waist until fully flexed. Raise, or extend waist until torso is parallel to legs. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Seated Row
exercise.execution: Pull cable attachment to waist while straightening lower back. Pull shoulders back and push chest forward while arching back. Return until arms are extended, shoulders are stretched forward, and lower back is flexed forward. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Wide Grip Seated Row
exercise.execution: Pull cable attachment to waist while pulling torso upright. Pull shoulders back and push chest forward while arching back. Return until arms are extended, shoulders are stretched forward, and lower back is flexed forward. Repeat.

exercise.name: Back Extension (on stability ball, arms down)
exercise.execution: Raise torso off of ball by hyperextending spine. Lower torso onto ball allowing spine to flex. Repeat.

exercise.name: Back Extension (on stability ball, arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Raise torso off of ball by hyperextending spine. Lower torso onto ball allowing spine to flex. Repeat.

exercise.name: Back Extension (on stability ball, arms up)
exercise.execution: Raise torso off of ball and hands over head by hyperextending spine. Lower torso onto ball allowing spine to flex with arms being lowered toward floor. Repeat.

exercise.name: Bird Dog
exercise.execution: Raise arm out straight beside head while raising and extending leg on opposite side up out behind body. Lower arm and leg to floor to original position and repeat. Perform movement with opposite arm and leg.

exercise.name: Alternating Bird Dog
exercise.execution: Raise left arm out straight beside head while raising and extending right leg up out behind body. Lower arm and leg to floor to original position. Repeat by raising and lowering right arm and left leg in same manner. Repeat by alternating between opposite sides.

exercise.name: Bird Dog (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Raise arm and torso upward beside head while raising leg on opposite side up out behind body. Lower arm, torso, and leg to original position and repeat. Perform movement with opposite arm and leg.

exercise.name: Alternating Bird Dog (on exercise ball)
exercise.execution: Raise left arm and torso upward beside head while raising right leg up behind body. Lower arm, torso, and leg to original position and repeat. Repeat by raising and lowering right arm and left leg in same manner. Repeat by alternating between opposite sides.

exercise.name: Hanging Hyperextension
exercise.execution: Raise hips up as high as possible by extending hips and spine. Lower hips to original position just above floor. Repeat.

exercise.name: Hyperextension (hands behind hips)
exercise.execution: Raise upper body until hips and waist are extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is vertical. Repeat.

exercise.name: Hyperextension (arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Raise upper body until hips and waist are extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is vertical. Repeat.

exercise.name: Hyperextension (hands on head)
exercise.execution: Raise upper body until hips and waist are extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is vertical. Repeat.

exercise.name: 45° Hyperextension (hands behind hips)
exercise.execution: Raise upper body until hips and waist are extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is approximately perpendicular to legs. Repeat.

exercise.name: 45° Hyperextension (arms crossed)
exercise.execution: Raise upper body until hips and waist are fully extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is approximately perpendicular to legs. Repeat.

exercise.name: 45° Hyperextension (hands behind neck)
exercise.execution: Raise upper body until hips and waist are extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is approximately perpendicular to legs. Repeat.

exercise.name: 45° Hyperextension (arms up)
exercise.execution: Raise upper body until hips and waist are extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is approximately perpendicular to legs. Repeat.

exercise.name: Superman
exercise.execution: Slowly raise upper body and legs off floor. Return upper body and legs to floor and repeat.

exercise.name: Contralateral Superman
exercise.execution: Raise left arm and shoulder and right leg up off floor. Lower arm and shoulder and leg to floor. Repeat by raising and lowering right arm and shoulder and left leg. Repeat by alternating between opposite sides.

exercise.name: Suspended Hyperextension
exercise.execution: Drive hips forward until hips are straight, while keeping arms and shoulders straight. Near top of motion, reach back with arms over head and hyperextend spine. While keeping arms over head, lower body with hips falling back down to starting position and repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Pull Through
exercise.execution: Pull hips back while flexing spine in C shape. Raise hips up high by straightening spine and hips until straight.

exercise.name: Rear Bridge
exercise.execution: Raise hips up off floor until hips are straight. Hold position.

exercise.name: Decline Rear Bridge
exercise.execution: Raise hips up off floor until hips are straight. Hold position.

exercise.name: Single Leg Decline Rear Bridge
exercise.execution: While keeping leg straight inline with body, raise hips up off floor until hip of bent leg is straight. Hold position. Change position and repeat hold on opposite side.

exercise.name: Incline Rear Bridge
exercise.execution: Raise hips up off floor until hips are straight. Hold position.

exercise.name: Cat Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Flex spine by hunching back up. Hold stretch.

exercise.name: Cat Movement
exercise.mechanic: Flex spine by hunching back up. Extend spine by arching back. Repeat.

exercise.name: Bent-over Cat Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Flex spine by hunching back up. Hold stretch.

exercise.name: Lever Lower Back Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Push and lower seat back. Hold stretch.

exercise.name: Lying Lower Back Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Pull knees toward shoulders allowing hips to be raised further off floor. Hold stretch.

exercise.name: Seated Lower Back Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Reach forward between feet. Hold stretch.

exercise.name: Seated Bent-over Lower Back Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Reach to floor under back of chair. Hold stretch.

exercise.name: Squatting Lower Back Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Keeping feet flat on floor, squat down as low as possible and bend down with arms straight. Lean back slightly and allow shoulders to stretch forward. Hold stretch.

exercise.name: Plow Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Allow knees to drop toward floor to sides of head. Hold stretch.

exercise.name: Barbell Bent Knee Good-morning
exercise.execution: Bend hips to lower torso forward until parallel to floor. Bend knees slightly during descent. Raise torso until hips are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Seated Good-morning
exercise.execution: Keeping back straight, bend torso forward as low as possible by bending hips. Raise torso until torso is upright. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Deadlift
exercise.execution: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Block Pull
exercise.execution: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Deficit Deadlift
exercise.execution: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return weights to floor by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Rack Pull
exercise.execution: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Sumo Deadlift
exercise.execution: Pull bar up by driving feet outward while pulling chest up. Extend knees when bar passes knees. At top of lift, when torso is upright, drive shoulders back and chest up. Return weight to floor by bending hips back and knees pointed outward, while keeping chest high and back straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Sumo Block Pull
exercise.execution: Pull bar up by driving feet outward while pulling chest up. Extend knees when bar passes knees. At top of lift, when torso is upright, drive shoulders back and chest up. Return weight to blocks by bending hips back and knees pointed outward, while keeping chest high and back straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Stiff Leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: Lower bar to top of feet by bending hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight, flexing only slightly at bottom. With knees bent, lift bar by extending at hips until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Extend knees at top if desired. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Single Leg Stiff-leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: Lower bar to floor while raising lifted leg back behind. Keep back straight and knee of supporting leg slightly bent. Keep hip and knee of lifted leg extended throughout movement. Once stretch is felt or barbell contacts floor, return to original position by raising torso while lowering lifted leg. Straighten knee of supporting leg as torso becomes upright. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Straight-back Stiff-leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: With back straight, lower bar to top of feet by bending hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight. Place weight onto floor. With knees still bent, lift bar by straightening hips until standing upright. Pull shoulders back if rounded. Extend knees at top if desired. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Hip Thrust
exercise.execution: Raise bar upward by extending hips until straight. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Lunge
exercise.execution: Lunge forward with first leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Barbell Alternating Lunge & Rear Lunge
exercise.execution: Lunge forward with right leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of right front leg until knee of rear left leg is almost in contact with floor. Forcibly extending hip and knee of forward right leg to return to original standing position.

exercise.name: Barbell Alternating Lunge To Rear Lunge
exercise.execution: Lunge forward with right leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of right front leg until knee of rear left leg is almost in contact with floor. Forcibly extending hip and knee of forward right leg to return to upright position. Instead of returning right foot to side of left foot, instead continue to step back with right leg while bending supporting left leg. Plant right forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting left leg until knee of rear right leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to standing position by extending hip and knee of supporting left leg and return rear right leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Barbell Rear Lunge
exercise.execution: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Barbell Side Lunge
exercise.execution: Lunge to one side with first leg. Land on heel, then on forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of lead leg, keeping knee pointed same direction of foot. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of lead leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Barbell Walking Lunge
exercise.execution: Step forward with first leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Stand on forward leg with assistance of rear leg. Lunge forward with opposite leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite legs.

exercise.name: Barbell Single Leg Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Barbell Single Leg Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Barbell Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Barbell Squat (low bar)
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend hips and knees until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Box Squat
exercise.execution: Sit back onto box by bending hips back while bending knees, keeping shins nearly perpendicular or knees slightly behind ankles. Lower rear end back onto box in controlled manner. Rock torso back slightly. Once torso rocks forward, immediately stand back up rapidly by driving hips upward, keeping knees above ankles and chest high until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Front Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Full Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until knees and hips are fully bent. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Hack Squat
exercise.execution: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Squat down by bending knees forward while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are close to parallel to floor and bar is behind lower leg. Repeat.

exercise.name: Safety Barbell Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend slightly forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand by extending hips and knees until legs are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Safety Barbell Squat (long handles)
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend slightly forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand with or without assistance of arms, extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Safety Barbell Squat (self-spotting)
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand with or without assistance of arms, extending hips and knees until legs are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Trap Bar Squat
exercise.execution: Lift weight upward by extending knees and hips until straight. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return weight to floor by bending hips back, while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Squat (with chains)
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend hips and knees until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Zercher Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight, hands close to body, and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are near parallel. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Step-up
exercise.execution: Place foot of first leg on bench. Stand on bench by extending hip and knee of first leg and place foot of second leg on bench. Step down with second leg by flexing hip and knee of first leg. Return to original standing position by placing foot of first leg to floor. Repeat first step with opposite leg alternating first steps between legs.

exercise.name: Barbell Lateral Step-up
exercise.execution: Lift leg and place foot on bench to side and forward of straight knee. Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning feet to original position. Repeat with opposite leg, alternating between legs.

exercise.name: Trap Bar Deadlift
exercise.execution: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Trap Bar Stiff Leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: Lower bar by bending hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight, flexing only slightly at bottom. With knees bent, lift bar by extending at hips until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Extend knees at top if desired. Repeat.

exercise.name: Trap Bar Straight-back Stiff-leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: With back straight, lower bar toward floor by bending at hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight. Place weight onto floor. With knees still bent, lift bar by extending at hips until standing upright. Pull shoulders back if rounded. Extend knees at top if desired. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Glute Kickback
exercise.execution: Pull cable attachment back by extending hip and knee. Return leg to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Cable Rear Lunge
exercise.execution: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Cable Rear Step-down Lunge
exercise.execution: Extend one leg back on forefoot. Lower body on other leg by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with lower platform. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat by alternating rear lunge with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Cable Single Leg Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Cable One Arm Single Leg Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Cable Split Squat (belt)
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original straddle position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with legs in opposite position.

exercise.name: Cable Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original straddle position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with legs in opposite position.

exercise.name: Cable One Arm Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original straddle position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with legs in opposite position.

exercise.name: Cable Squat
exercise.execution: Keeping chest high and back straight, raise stirrups by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Squat down until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Bar Squat
exercise.execution: Stand up by extending hips and knees until legs are straight. Squat back down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend slightly forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Belt Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Squat up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Standing Hip Extension
exercise.execution: Pull cable attachment back by extending hip. Return leg to original position. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Cable Bent-over Hip Extension
exercise.execution: Pull cable attachment back by extending hip. Return leg to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Cable Step-up
exercise.execution: Place foot of first leg on elevated platform. Stand on elevated platform by extending hip and knee of first leg and place foot of second leg on bench. Step down with second leg by flexing hip and knee of first leg. Return to original standing position by placing foot of first leg to lower position. Repeat first step with opposite leg alternating first steps between legs.

exercise.name: Cable Stiff Leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: Bow forward by bending hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight, flexing low back at bottom. With knees slightly bent, raise torso by extending at waist, then hips, gradually extending knees until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Straight-back Stiff-leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: With back straight, bow forward by bending hips and bend knees slightly during descent. Raise torso by extending hips while gradually extending knees until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Lunge
exercise.execution: Lunge forward with first leg. Land on heel then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Alternating Side Lunge
exercise.execution: Lunge to one side with first leg. Position closest dumbbell behind thigh and opposite dumbbell to front. Land on heel then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of lead leg, keeping knee pointed same direction of foot. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of lead leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Rear Lunge
exercise.execution: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Side Lunge
exercise.execution: Lunge to one side with first leg. Position closest dumbbell behind thigh and opposite dumbbell to front. Land on heel then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of lead leg, keeping knee pointed same direction of foot. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of lead leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Walking Lunge
exercise.execution: Step forward with first leg. Land on heel then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Stand on forward leg with assistance of rear leg. Lunge forward with opposite leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite legs.

exercise.name: Dumbell Single Leg Stiff-leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: Lower dumbells to floor while raising lifted leg back behind. Keep back straight and knee of supporting leg slightly bend. Keep hip and knee of lifted leg extended throughout movement. Once stretch is felt or dumbells contacts floor, return to original position by raising torso while lowering lifted leg. Straighten knee of supporting leg as torso becomes upright. Repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Single Leg Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Single Leg Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Front Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Step-up
exercise.execution: Place foot of first leg on bench. Stand on bench by extending hip and knee of first leg and place foot of second leg on bench. Step down with second leg by flexing hip and knee of first leg. Return to original standing position by placing foot of first leg to floor. Repeat first step with opposite leg, alternating first steps between legs.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Lateral Step-up
exercise.execution: Lift leg and place foot on bench to side and forward of straight knee. Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning feet to original position. Repeat with opposite leg alternating between legs.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Step Down
exercise.execution: Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning foot off of bench to floor and repeat. Continue with opposite position.

exercise.name: Lever Bent-over Glute Kickback (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Push platform back by extending leg back. Return leg to original position. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Deadlift (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Lift lever by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Stiff Leg Deadlift (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Bow forward by bending hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight, flexing low back at bottom. With knees slightly bent, raise torso by extending at waist, then hips, gradually extending knees until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Straight-back Stiff-leg Deadlift (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: With back straight, bow forward by bending hips and bend knees slightly during descent. Raise torso by extending hips while gradually extending knees until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Hip Thrust
exercise.execution: Raise weight upward by extending hips until straight. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Hip Thrust (on lying leg curl machine)
exercise.execution: Raise padded roller upward by extending hips until straight. Lower and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever 45° Leg Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Flex hips and knees to lower lever until hips are completely flexed. Push platform by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Single Leg 45° Leg Press
exercise.execution: Lower platform by bending leg until knee is just short of complete flexion. Return by extending knee and hip. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Hack Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Lower seat by flex hips and knees until either is near complete flexion. Raise seat by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Lying Leg Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Push lever platform away by extending hips and knees until knees are straight. Return lever platform by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion or until hips are completely flexed. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Lying Leg Press (custom - plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Push lever platform by extending hips and knees until knees are straight. Lower lever platform by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Single Leg Lying Leg Press (custom - plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Push platform away by extending hip and knee. Return by bending leg until knee or hip is just short of complete flexion. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Leg Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Push platform(s) away by extending knees and hips until knees are fully extended. Return until hips are completely flexed. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Alternating Seated Leg Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Push one platform away by extending knee and hip. Return to original position. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue by alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Lever Single Leg Seated Leg Press (plate loaded)
Lever Lying Hip Extension (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Extend hips and knees until legs are straight. Return to original position by flexing hips and knees. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Power Runner (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Push forward pedal back by extending leg while allowing other pedal to come forward by bending opposite leg. Continue pedalling by alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Lever Rear Lunge (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Lever Barbell Rear Lunge (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Lever Reverse Hyper-extension (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Raise lever by extending hips as high as possible with legs nearly straight. Lower legs to original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Single Leg Split Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: With chest high, lift lever by extending hips and knees to full extension. Return until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Barbell Single Leg Split Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Single Leg Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Bend knee forward slightly while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knee pointed same direction of foot. Squat down as low as possible. Extend knee and hip until leg is straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Split Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: With chest high, lift lever by extending hips and knees to full extension. Return until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Barbell Split Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Lower body on other leg by flexing knees and hips of of both legs until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original straddled position by extending hips and knees of both legs. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Sliding Split Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Lower lever downward by sliding platform back and squatting down on forward leg. Keep chest high as hips descend to knee height. Lift sliding forward and extending hips and knee to full extension. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend by bending knees and hip until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Lift lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend by bending knees and hip until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Lift lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Barbell Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Front Squat
exercise.execution: Lower lever by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Lift lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Full Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until knees and hips are fully bent. Lift lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Hack Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Lower lever by bending hips and knees, until knees are just short of complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever V-Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Bend knees forward slightly while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until hips are just short of complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Bent-over Hip Extension
exercise.execution: Push foot lever back by extending hip. Return leg to original position. Repeat. Reposition and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Kneeling Hip Extension
exercise.execution: Keeping one leg on shin pad, extend hip of other leg and push roller pad back. Raise roller pad up until hip is completely extended. Return leg to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Alternating Kneeling Hip Extension
exercise.execution: Keeping one leg on shin pad, extending hip of other leg and push roller pad back. Raise roller pad up until hip is completely extended. Return leg to original position. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue alternating between each side.

exercise.name: Lever Lying Hip Extension
exercise.execution: Push padded leg bar down until hips are extended. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Alternating Lying Hip Extension
exercise.execution: Raise one knee by flexing hip. Return to original position by extending hip. Repeat with opposite leg, alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Lever Standing Hip Extension
exercise.execution: Lower lever by extending hip. Return until knee is higher than hip. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Standing Hip Extension (with abdominal pad)
exercise.execution: Extend lever back by extending hip and straightening leg. Return by flexing hip and knee. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Alternating Lying Leg Press
exercise.execution: Lower one lever platform toward body by bending knee and hip until weight taps or nearly taps unused portion of weight stack. Push lever platform away by extending knee and hip. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue by alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Leg Press
exercise.execution: Extend knees and hips until knees are fully extended. Return until hips are completely flexed. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Single Leg Seated Leg Press
exercise.execution: Push platform away by extending hip and knee. Return by bending leg until knee or hip is just short of complete flexion. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Bent-over Glute Kickback
exercise.execution: Push platform or pedal back by extending leg. Return leg to original position. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Kneeling Glute Kickback
exercise.execution: Push platform back by extending leg back. Return leg to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Standing Glute Kickback
exercise.execution: Push platform down by extending leg until straight. Return leg to original position. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg positions.

exercise.name: Lever Squat
exercise.execution: Raise lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever V-Squat
exercise.execution: Raise lever by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Squat down with knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until knees or hips are near complete flexion. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Split V-Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down with knee pointed same direction as foot. Allow leg to bend behind with forefoot on floor. Descend until forward hip is near complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knee and hip until leg is straight. Repeat. Continue with other leg.

exercise.name: Lever Single Leg Split V-Squat
exercise.execution: Raise lever by extending knees and hips. Lower lever by flexing hips and knees until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg positions.

exercise.name: Lever Alternating Single Leg Split V-Squat
exercise.execution: Transfer right foot back to inside of rear vertical platform. Lower lever by flexing hips and knees until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Raise lever by extending knees and hips until knee is straight. Return right foot to original position by other foot. Repeat with opposite leg movement and continue alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Sled 45° Leg Press
exercise.execution: Lower sled by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion or until hips are completely flexed. Return by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Alternating 45° Leg Press
exercise.execution: Lower one platform toward body by bending knee and hip until knees are just short of complete flexion or until hips are completely flexed. Push platform away by extending knee and hip. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue by alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Sled Single Leg 45° Leg Press
exercise.execution: Lower sled by bending leg until knee is just short of complete flexion. Return by extending knee and hip. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Sled Hack Press
exercise.execution: Lower sled by flexing hips and knees until either is near complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Lying Leg Press
exercise.execution: Extend hips and knees. Return until hips are completely flexed. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Lying Leg Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Bring sled toward platform by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion or until hips are completely flexed. Return by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Single Leg Lying Leg Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Bring sled toward platform by flexing hip and knee of supporting leg until knee is just short of complete flexion or until hip is completely flexed. Return by extending knee and hip. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Sled Single Leg Lying Leg Press
exercise.execution: Push platform by extending knee and hip until knee is straight. Return by bending hip and knee of supporting leg until knee is just short of complete flexion or until hip is completely flexed. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Sled Seated Leg Press
exercise.execution: Extend knees and hips until knees are fully extended. Return until hips are completely flexed. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Vertical Leg Press
exercise.execution: Lower sled by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion or just before hips raise up from pad. Return by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Single Leg Vertical Leg Press
exercise.execution: Lower sled by flexing leg until knees are just short of complete flexion or just before hips raise up from pad. Push weight up by extending knee and hip. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Sled Kneeling Glute Kickback
exercise.execution: Push foot bar up by extending leg back as far as possible. Return leg to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Sled Standing Glute Kickback
exercise.execution: Push platform back by extending leg back until straight. Return leg to original position. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Sled Rear Lunge
exercise.execution: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs, alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Sled Squat
exercise.execution: If hand or lever lock is available, disengage weight, squat to lowest position and re-engage lock. Lift sled by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Lower sled by bending knees forward slightly while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Hack Squat
exercise.execution: Lower sled by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed. Raise sled by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Single Leg Hack Squat
exercise.execution: Lower sled by flexing hips and knee of supporting leg until knees are just short of complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knee and hips. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Smith Bent Knee Good-morning
exercise.execution: Bend hips to lower torso forward until parallel to floor. Bend knees slightly during descent. Raise torso until hips are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Deadlift
exercise.execution: Squat down to lower bar by bending hips and knees. Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Stiff Leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: With knees slightly bent, Lower bar toward top of feet by bending hips. Keep waist straight, flexing only slightly at bottom. Lift bar by extending at hips until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Extend knees at top if desired. Repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Straight-back Stiff-leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: With knees bent, lower bar toward top feet by bending hips and keeping waist straight. Lift bar by extending at hips until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Extend knees at top if desired. Repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Rear Lunge
exercise.execution: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs, alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Smith Single Leg Split Squat
exercise.execution: Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Smith Split Squat
exercise.execution: Lower body on other leg by flexing knees and hips of both legs until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original straddled position by extending hips and knees of both legs. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Smith Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Single Leg Squat
exercise.execution: Bend knee slightly forward while allowing hips to bend, keeping back straight and knee pointed same direction of foot. Descend until thigh of supporting leg is just past parallel to floor. Extend knee and hip until leg is straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Front Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward , keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Hack Squat
