exercise.execution: Squat down by bending knees forward while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are too close to parallel to floor and bar is behind lower leg. Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Wide Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Belt Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Squat up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Front Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Reverse Hyper-extension
exercise.execution: Raise weight by extending hips as high as possible until legs are nearly straight. Lower legs to original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Single Leg Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Kettlebell Front Squat
exercise.execution: Bend knees slightly forward while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back taut and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Kettlebell Overhead Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly, until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Clean and Jerk weight with opposite arm and squat with other leg forward.

exercise.name: Kettlebell Overhead Rear Lunge
exercise.execution: Step back with leg on opposite side of kettlebell while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat. Clean and Jerk weight with opposite arm and lunge on other leg.

exercise.name: Lunge
exercise.execution: Lunge forward with first leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Rear Lunge
exercise.execution: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Reverse Hyper-extension
exercise.execution: Raise legs by extending hips as high as possible until legs are nearly straight. Lower legs to original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Reverse Hyper-extension (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Holding firmly on anchor, extend legs upward by lifting and straightening leg as high as possible. Lower legs to original position with thighs close to stability ball. Repeat.

exercise.name: Single Leg Hip Bridge
exercise.execution: Raise body by extending hip of bent leg, keeping extended leg and hip straight. Return to original position by lowering body with extended leg and hip straight. Repeat and continue with opposite sides.

exercise.name: Single Leg Squat (pistol)
exercise.execution: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back as straight as possible and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Single Leg Box Squat (pistol)
exercise.execution: Squat down while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Once bottocks makes contact with bench or box, raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Single Leg Partial Box Squat (pistol)
exercise.execution: Squat down while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Once buttock makes contact with bench or box, raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Single Leg Squat (with leg back)
exercise.execution: Squat down as far as possible while keeping raised leg from contacting floor as far down as possible. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. In lowest position, gently place elevated lower leg on floor. Raise body back up with minimal assistance from raised leg on floor. Stand to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg are straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Single Leg Half Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down to challenging depth while keeping raised leg from contacting floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Stand back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg are straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Single Leg Reclining Squat (bar)
exercise.execution: While reclining back, squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as suppor ting foot. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Single Leg Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Single Leg Stiff-leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: Lower torso forward and downward while raising lifted leg back behind. Keep back straight and knee of supporting leg slightly bend. Keep hip and knee of lifted leg extended throughout movement. Once stretch is felt or hands contact floor, return to original position by raising torso while lowering lifted leg. Straighten knee of supporting leg as torso becomes upright. Repeat.

exercise.name: Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Squat up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Half Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend to height which allows prescribed number of reps at suggested intensity, short of thighs descending just past parallel to floor. Stand up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return to standing position and repeat.

exercise.name: Balance Board Squat
exercise.execution: Extend arms forward in front of body. Squat down by bending knees slightly forward while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Squat up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Step-up
exercise.execution: Place foot of first leg on bench. Stand on bench by extending hip and knee of first leg and place foot of second leg on bench. Step down with second leg by flexing hip and knee of first leg. Return to original standing position by placing foot of first leg to floor. Repeat first step with opposite leg, alternating first steps between legs.

exercise.name: Lateral Step-up
exercise.execution: Lift leg and place foot on bench to side and forward of straight knee. Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning feet to original position. Repeat with opposite leg, alternating between legs.

exercise.name: Step-down
exercise.execution: Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning foot off of bench to floor and repeat. Continue with opposite position.

exercise.name: Alternating Step-down
exercise.execution: Step down with first foot to side of elevated surface onto floor. Stand back up on elevated surface by straightening upper leg and pushing body upward. Place foot to original position next to opposite foot. Step down and back up with opposite leg in same manner. Repeat by alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Self-assisted Single Leg Squat (bar)
exercise.execution: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as supporting foot. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Self-assisted Single Leg Reclining Squat (pole)
exercise.execution: Squat down while keeping leg elevated off of floor. With arms slightly flexed, lean back slightly while only allowing knee to travel slightly forward. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as supporting foot. Descend to lowest position. Raise body back up to original position while keeping knee behind bar and arms slightly flexed until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Self-assisted Single Leg Squat (leg wrapped)
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending knee forward and hip back behind. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Descend until thigh is just past parallel to floor. Return to standing position with minimal assistance from wrapped leg. Stand to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg are straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Self-assisted Squat
exercise.execution: While holding onto horizontal bar, squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return to standing position and repeat.

exercise.name: Self-assisted Squat (on suspension trainer)
exercise.execution: While holding onto suspension trainer handles, squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return to standing position and repeat.

exercise.name: Self-assisted Step-down
exercise.execution: Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning foot off of bench to floor and repeat. Continue with opposite position.

exercise.name: Suspended Hip Bridge
exercise.execution: Raise hips up by extending hips until fully extended. Lower hips until hips and back make contact with mat. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Reclining Squat
exercise.execution: While reclined back and holding onto suspension trainer handles, squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward while keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are perpendicular to body's angle of movement. Stand up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return to reclined standing position with body straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Single Leg Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back, up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Suspended Single Leg Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Suspended Single Leg Split Squat (self-assisted)
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of supporting leg. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Glute Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Push and lower seat back. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lying Glute Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Pull leg toward torso. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lying Glute Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Pull leg toward torso. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite leg.

exercise.name: PNF Lying Glute Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Extend or place hands on mat to each side of participant. Push participant's leg by leaning toward participant. Repeat with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Towel Lying Glute Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Pull both ends of towel so leg travels toward torso. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lying Wall Glute Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Bend knee of straight leg while lowering heel on wall. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Prone Glute Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Allow body to ease down toward floor with support of arms. Hold stretch and repeat with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Seated Bent-over Glute Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Reach or slide forward with support of arms and hold stretch. Repeat with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Seated Glute Stretch (bench)
exercise.mechanic: Lean down, lowering torso toward thighs. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Seated Glute Stretch (chair)
exercise.mechanic: Lean down, lowering torso toward thighs. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Seated Glute Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Bring torso upright by walking hands closer to hips, keeping arms straight. Lean forward and hold stretch. Repeat with opposite leg.

exercise.name: PNF Seated Glute Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Push participant's torso toward legs. Hold stretch. Repeat with legs in opposite position

exercise.name: Standing Glute Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Lean down, lowering torso toward thighs. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Squatting Glute Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Squat lower and lean forward toward crossed leg. Hold stretch . Repeat with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Knee Hug
exercise.mechanic: Pull knee toward body until stretch is felt in hip. Release and step forward with stretched leg. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue by alternating stretch and step between each leg until specific distance is covered or desired number of repetitions have been completed.

exercise.name: Walking Ankle Grab
exercise.mechanic: Pull foot and lower leg upward until stretch is felt in hip. Release and step forward with stretched leg. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue by alternating stretch and step between each leg until specific distance is covered or desired number of repetitions have been completed.

exercise.name: Cable Hip Abduction
exercise.execution: Move leg to opposite side of low pulley by abduction hip. Return and repeat. Turn around and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Cable Lying Hip Internal Rotation
exercise.execution: Keeping knee of attached leg bent approximately 90°, pull cable attachment away from pulley by rotating hip as far as possible. Return leg to original position toward pulley and repeat. Place ankle cuff on opposite leg and continue lying opposite direction.

exercise.name: Cable Seated Hip Internal Rotation
exercise.execution: Keeping knee of attached leg bent approximately 90°, pull cable attachment away from pulley by rotating hip as far as possible. Return foot behind stationary foot and toward pulley. Repeat. Place ankle cuff on opposite leg and continue facing opposite direction.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Lying Hip Abduction
exercise.execution: Raise weighted leg up off ground as high as possible, keeping dumbbell positioned on side of upper thigh. Return to leg to floor and repeat. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Hip Abduction (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Move legs away from one another as far as possible. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Kneeling Hip Internal Rotation (on hip abduction machine)
exercise.execution: Pull levers apart as far as possible with legs by externally rotating hips. Return until feet make contact, then repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Lying Hip Abduction
exercise.execution: Move legs away from one another by abduction hip. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Hip Abduction
exercise.execution: Move legs apart as far as possible. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Standing Hip Abduction
exercise.execution: Raise leg against roller pad to side by abduction hip. Return and repeat. Reposition roller pad lever and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Weighted Lying Hip Abduction
exercise.execution: Raise weighted leg up off ground as high as possible. Balance bar on side of foot while holding onto closest side of bar. Return to floor and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Cable Push Pull
exercise.execution: Pull low pulley stirrup back to side of ribcage while pushing high pulley stirrup forward until arm is extended, allowing torso to rotate to opposite side.

exercise.name: Cable Twist
exercise.execution: Keeping arms straight, rotate torso to opposite side until cable makes contact with shoulder. Return to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite side.

exercise.name: Side Bridge Hip Abduction
exercise.execution: Keeping side of bottom foot on ground, raise hips up off ground while raising upper leg upward away from lower leg. Return to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Angled Side Bridge Hip Abduction
exercise.execution: Keeping foot closest to bar on ground, raise hips upward and away from bar while raising leg furthest from bar upward away from lower leg. Return to original position with hips sagging downward and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Bent Knee Side Bridge Hip Abduction
exercise.execution: Keeping shank of lower leg on mat or floor, raise hips up off ground while raising upper leg upward away from lower leg. Return to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Suspended Hip Abduction
exercise.execution: Pull legs apart as far as possible. Return by placing legs together and repeat.

exercise.name: Angled Side Bridge
exercise.execution: Raise hips upward by lateral flexion of spine. Lower to original position and repeat. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Bent Knee Side Bridge
exercise.execution: Raise hips upward by lateral flexion of spine. Lower to original position and repeat. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Side Bridge
exercise.execution: Raise hips upward by lateral flexion of spine. Lower to original position and repeat. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Suspended Side Bend
exercise.execution: Lower hips away from direction of suspension trainer anchor by laterally flexing spine. Return to original upright position and repeat. Reposition body facing opposite direction. Continue with other side.

exercise.name: Suspended Side Bridge
exercise.execution: Raise hips upward by lateral flexion of spine. Lower to original position and repeat. Reposition to opposite side and continue.

exercise.name: Suspended Twist
exercise.execution: While keeping arms straight and shoulders fixed, rotate torso up to one side. Twist until upright or slight stretch is felt in waist, whichever comes soonest. Rotate back to starting position and repeat. Continue on opposite side.

exercise.name: Lying Crossover Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Lower leg to opposite side toward hand. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: PNF Lying Crossover Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Push participant's knee to opposite side while backing participant's shoulder down. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Lying Pretzel Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Lower knee to opposite side, twisting waist so hip rolls to side. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Seated Hip Internal Rotator Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Push knee toward floor. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Seated Hip Internal Rotator Stretch (bent leg under)
exercise.mechanic: Straighten extended knee pushing bent knee toward floor. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Seated Hip Internal Rotator Stretch (chair or bench)
exercise.mechanic: Push knee toward downward. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Seated Pretzel Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Push side of knee with elbow so bent leg further crosses thigh of straight leg. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Side Pretzel Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Turn chest and front of pelvis further toward floor. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Lying Iliotibial Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Pull knee of rear leg back by straightening hip. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Squatting Iliotibial Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Squat with supporting leg while placing leg nearest wall behind and across supporting leg so foot is positioned away from wall. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Standing Iliotibial Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Maintaining complete extension of hip, shift body weight to rear leg allowing hip of leg in front to drop. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Wall Iliotibial Stretch
exercise.mechanic: With legs and hip straight, lower hip toward wall. Hold stretch . Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Cable Assisted Wheel Rollout
exercise.execution: With arms straight, roll wheel out as far as possible. Lower body gently to floor extending arms forward. Raise body back up by flexing hips and pulling arms back to original position. Return until hips are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Lying Leg Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until thighs are just past perpendicular to torso or before hips raise off of bench. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Lying Leg Raise (on bench)
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until thighs are past perpendicular to torso or before hips raise off of bench. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Lying Straight Leg Raise
exercise.execution: With knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until thighs are just past perpendicular to torso or before hips raise off of mat. Return until hips are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Standing Leg Raise
exercise.execution: Raise knee by flexing hip while allowing lower leg to bend back under resistance. When thigh is just beyond horizontal, lower leg until hip and knee is extended. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Cable Standing Straight Leg Raise
exercise.execution: Raise leg upward by flexing hip while keeping knee straight. Raise leg as high as possible. Lower leg to original starting position. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Hip Flexion
exercise.execution: Raise lever by flexing hip until knee is higher than hip. Return until hip is extended. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Lying Leg Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips until they are completely flexed. Lower legs until hips are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Vertical Leg Raise
exercise.execution: With back straight, raise legs as high as possible by flexing hips. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Decline Sit-up
exercise.execution: Lower body back until hips are almost extended. Raise body by flexing hips until torso is upright. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Hanging Leg Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed or knees are well above hips. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Hanging Straight Leg Raise
exercise.execution: With knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return until hips are extended downward. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Incline Leg Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Incline Leg Raise (arms on pads)
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Incline Straight Leg Raise
exercise.execution: With knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until thighs are just past perpendicular to torso. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Incline Straight Leg Raise (arms on pads)
exercise.execution: With knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until hips are flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Lying Leg Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Roman Chair Sit-up
exercise.execution: Lower body back until hips are almost extended. Raise body by flexing hips until torso is upright. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Seated Leg Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees while pulling torso slightly forward to maintain balance. Return by extending hips and knees and lean torso back to counter balance. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Vertical Leg Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed or knees are well above hips. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Vertical Leg Raise (on parallel bars)
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Vertical Straight Leg Raise
exercise.execution: With knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return until hips are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Hanging Leg Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed or knees are well above hips. Return until hips and knees are extended downward. Repeat.

exercise.name: Hanging Leg Raise (with ab straps)
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed or knees are well above hips. Return until hips and knees are extended downward. Repeat.

exercise.name: Hanging Straight Leg Raise
exercise.execution: With knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until hips are completely flexed or knees are well above hips. Return until hips are extended downward. Repeat.

exercise.name: Incline Leg Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Incline Leg Raise (arms on pads)
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Incline Straight Leg Raise
exercise.execution: With knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until hips are completely flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Incline Straight Leg Raise (arms on pads)
exercise.execution: With knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until hips are flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lying Leg Raise (on bench)
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until thighs are completely flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lying Simultaneous Alternating Leg Raise
exercise.execution: Simultaneously change positions of legs, lowering and straightening raised leg down just above floor while raising and bending lower leg to opposite position. Continue alternating leg positions.

exercise.name: Lying Leg Raise (on floor)
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until thighs are completely flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lying Straight Leg Raise
exercise.execution: Keeping knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until hips are completely flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lying Simultaneous Alternating Straight Leg Raise
exercise.execution: Keeping knees nearly straight, simultaneously change positions of legs so vertical leg is lowered while lower leg is raised vertically. Continue alternating leg positions.

exercise.name: Seated Leg Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees while pulling torso slightly forward to maintain balance. Return by extending hips and knees and lean torso back to counter balance. Repeat.

exercise.name: Vertical Leg Raise
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed or knees are well above hips. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Vertical Leg Raise (on parallel bars)
exercise.execution: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Vertical Straight Leg Raise
exercise.execution: With knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until thighs are just pass parallel to floor. Return until hips are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Jack-knife on Ball
exercise.execution: Bend hips and knees, allowing shins to roll over top of ball. Pull knees toward chest until heels are under or near glutes. Return by extending hips and knees to original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Roman Chair Sit-up
exercise.execution: Lower body back until hips are almost extended. Raise body by flexing hips until torso is upright. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lying Scissor Kick
exercise.execution: Keeping knees nearly straight, simultaneously change positions of legs so vertical leg is lowered while lower leg is raised vertically. Continue alternating leg positions.

exercise.name: Jack-knife on Power Wheel
exercise.execution: Bend hips and knees, pulling legs under body. Pull bent knees toward chest, allowing rear end to raise upward. Return by extending hips and knees to original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Wheel Rollout
exercise.execution: With arms straight, roll wheel out as far as possible. Lower body gently to floor extending arms forward. Raise body back up by flexing hips and pulling arms back to original position. Return until hips are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Pike on Power Wheel
exercise.execution: From plank position, raise rear end up as high as possible by bending hips. Pull power wheel toward hands while keeping knees straight. Return by extending hips to original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Pike on Discs
exercise.execution: From plank position, raise rear end up as high as possible by bending hips. Pull gliding discs toward hands while keeping knees straight. Return by extending hips to original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Mountain Climber
exercise.execution: Simultaneously alternate leg positions by straightening bent leg behind, while bending straight leg forward. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Pike
exercise.execution: Raise rear end up as high as possible by bending hips. Pull feet toward hands, while keeping knees straight. Return by extending hips to original straight body position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Bent-over Lunging Hip Flexor Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Straighten hip of rear leg by pushing hips down and forward. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Kneeling Hip Flexor Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Straighten hip of rear leg by pushing hips forward. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Lever Hip Flexor Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Squat down with back straight while straightening hip of rear leg by pushing hips forward. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Lunging Hip Flexor Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Squat down with chest high, straightening hip of rear leg by pushing hips down and forward. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Lunging Hip Flexor Stretch (on bench)
exercise.mechanic: Slowly lunge forward by continuing to bend forward leg. With chest high, straighten hip of rear leg by driving hips down and forward. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Lying Hip Flexor Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Allow lower thigh to drop toward floor. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Sled Kneeling Hip Flexor Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Squeeze release grips and slide padded leg support back until mild stretch is felt. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Standing Hip Flexor Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Slowly lunge forward by bending forward leg. With chest high, straighten hip of rear leg by pushing hips forward. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Lying Iliotibial Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Pull knee of rear leg back by straightening hip. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Squatting Iliotibial Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Squat with supporting leg while placing leg nearest wall behind and across supporting leg so foot is positioned away from wall. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Standing Iliotibial Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Maintaining complete extension of hip, shift body weight to rear leg allowing hip of leg in front to drop. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Wall Iliotibial Stretch
exercise.mechanic: With legs and hip straight, lower hip toward wall. Hold stretch . Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Walking Lunge
exercise.force: Stand upright with arms to sides.

exercise.name: Cable Lying Hip External Rotation
exercise.execution: Keeping knee of attached leg bent approximately 90°, pull cable attachment toward opposite knee by rotating hip. Return until slight stretch is felt in hip, then repeat. Place ankle cuff on opposite leg and continue lying opposite direction.

exercise.name: Cable Seated Hip External Rotation
exercise.execution: Keeping knee of attached leg bent approximately 90°, pull cable attachment under thigh of stationary leg by rotating hip. Return until slight stretch is felt in hip, then repeat. Place ankle cuff on opposite leg and continue facing opposite direction.

exercise.name: Lever Kneeling Hip External Rotation (on hip adduction machine)
exercise.execution: Push levers together with legs by externally rotating hips. Return until slight stretch is felt in hip, then repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Push Pull
exercise.execution: Pull low pulley stirrup back to side of ribcage while pushing high pulley stirrup forward until arm is extended, allowing torso to rotate to opposite side.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Hip Abduction
exercise.execution: Move legs apart as far as possible. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Hip Abduction (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Move legs away from one another as far as possible. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Twist
exercise.execution: While keeping arms straight and shoulders fixed, rotate torso up to one side. Twist until upright or slight stretch is felt in waist, whichever comes soonest. Rotate back to starting position and repeat. Continue on opposite side.

exercise.name: Lying Hip External Rotator Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Lower bent knee beside straight leg. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Seated Hip External Rotator Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Lower bent knee beside straight leg. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Lever Piriformis Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Push and lower seat back. Repeat with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lying Piriformis Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Pull leg toward torso. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lying Piriformis Stretch (single leg)
exercise.mechanic: Pull thigh toward torso while keeping knee over torso. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite leg.

exercise.name: PNF Lying Piriformis Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Push your bodyweight down on foot while pushing down on side of participant's knee. Hold stretch. Repeat with legs in opposite position.

exercise.name: Seated Piriformis Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Reposition hands forward with arms straight to place torso closer to legs. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Seated Piriformis Stretch (chair or bench)
exercise.mechanic: Lean forward pulling body toward legs. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite leg.

exercise.name: PNF Seated Piriformis Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Push participant's torso toward legs. Hold stretch. Repeat with legs in opposite position.

exercise.name: Barbell Lunge
exercise.execution: Lunge forward with first leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Barbell Alternating Lunge & Rear Lunge
exercise.execution: Lunge forward with right leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of right front leg until knee of rear left leg is almost in contact with floor. Forcibly extending hip and knee of forward right leg to return to original standing position.

exercise.name: Barbell Alternating Lunge To Rear Lunge
exercise.execution: Lunge forward with right leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of right front leg until knee of rear left leg is almost in contact with floor. Forcibly extending hip and knee of forward right leg to return to upright position. Instead of returning right foot to side of left foot, instead continue to step back with right leg while bending supporting left leg. Plant right forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting left leg until knee of rear right leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to standing position by extending hip and knee of supporting left leg and return rear right leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Barbell Rear Lunge
exercise.execution: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Barbell Side Lunge
exercise.execution: Lunge to one side with first leg. Land on heel, then on forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of lead leg, keeping knee pointed same direction of foot. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of lead leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Barbell Walking Lunge
exercise.execution: Step forward with first leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Stand on forward leg with assistance of rear leg. Lunge forward with opposite leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite legs.

exercise.name: Barbell Single Leg Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Barbell Single Leg Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Barbell Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Barbell Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Front Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Full Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until knees and hips are fully bent. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Hack Squat
exercise.execution: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Squat down by bending knees forward while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are close to parallel to floor and bar is behind lower leg. Repeat.

exercise.name: Safety Barbell Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend slightly forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand by extending hips and knees until legs are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Safety Barbell Squat (long handles)
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend slightly forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand with or without assistance of arms, extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Safety Barbell Squat (self-spotting)
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand with or without assistance of arms, extending hips and knees until legs are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Trap Bar Squat
exercise.execution: Lift weight upward by extending knees and hips until straight. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return weight to floor by bending hips back, while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Squat (with chains)
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend hips and knees until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Zercher Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight, hands close to body, and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are near parallel. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Step-up
exercise.execution: Place foot of first leg on bench. Stand on bench by extending hip and knee of first leg and place foot of second leg on bench. Step down with second leg by flexing hip and knee of first leg. Return to original standing position by placing foot of first leg to floor. Repeat first step with opposite leg alternating first steps between legs.

exercise.name: Barbell Lateral Step-up
exercise.execution: Lift leg and place foot on bench to side and forward of straight knee. Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning feet to original position. Repeat with opposite leg, alternating between legs.

exercise.name: Cable Rear Lunge
exercise.execution: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Cable Rear Step-down Lunge
exercise.execution: Extend one leg back on forefoot. Lower body on other leg by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with lower platform. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat by alternating rear lunge with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Cable Single Leg Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Cable One Arm Single Leg Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Cable Split Squat (belt)
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original straddle position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with legs in opposite position.

exercise.name: Cable Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original straddle position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with legs in opposite position.

exercise.name: Cable One Arm Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original straddle position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with legs in opposite position.

exercise.name: Cable Squat
exercise.execution: Keeping chest high and back straight, raise stirrups by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Squat down until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Bar Squat
exercise.execution: Stand up by extending hips and knees until legs are straight. Squat back down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend slightly forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Belt Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Squat up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Belt Half Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until weight stack taps or comes very close from making contact. Keeping chest high and back straight, raise back up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Standing Leg Extension
exercise.execution: Keeping thigh stationary, extend lower leg forward until leg is straight. Return by lowering lower leg down and back to original position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Cable Step Down
exercise.execution: Raise body by extending knee and hip on platform until leg is straight. Return until foot of lower leg makes contact with lower platform or floor and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Cable Step-up
exercise.execution: Place foot of first leg on elevated platform. Stand on elevated platform by extending hip and knee of first leg and place foot of second leg on bench. Step down with second leg by flexing hip and knee of first leg. Return to original standing position by placing foot of first leg to lower position. Repeat first step with opposite leg alternating first steps between legs.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Lunge
exercise.execution: Lunge forward with first leg. Land on heel then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Alternating Side Lunge
exercise.execution: Lunge to one side with first leg. Position closest dumbbell behind thigh and opposite dumbbell to front. Land on heel then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of lead leg, keeping knee pointed same direction of foot. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of lead leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Rear Lunge
exercise.execution: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Side Lunge
exercise.execution: Lunge to one side with first leg. Position closest dumbbell behind thigh and opposite dumbbell to front. Land on heel then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of lead leg, keeping knee pointed same direction of foot. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of lead leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Walking Lunge
exercise.execution: Step forward with first leg. Land on heel then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Stand on forward leg with assistance of rear leg. Lunge forward with opposite leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite legs.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Single Leg Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Single Leg Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Front Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Step-up
exercise.execution: Place foot of first leg on bench. Stand on bench by extending hip and knee of first leg and place foot of second leg on bench. Step down with second leg by flexing hip and knee of first leg. Return to original standing position by placing foot of first leg to floor. Repeat first step with opposite leg, alternating first steps between legs.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Lateral Step-up
exercise.execution: Lift leg and place foot on bench to side and forward of straight knee. Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning feet to original position. Repeat with opposite leg alternating between legs.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Step Down
exercise.execution: Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning foot off of bench to floor and repeat. Continue with opposite position.

exercise.name: Lever Leg Extension (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Move lever forward and upward by extending knees until legs are straight. Return lever to original position by bending knees. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Alternating Leg Extension (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Move one lever forward and upward by extending one knee until leg is straight. Lower to original position. Repeat with opposite side. Continue to alternate between sides.

exercise.name: Lever 45° Leg Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Flex hips and knees to lower lever until hips are completely flexed. Push platform by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Single Leg 45° Leg Press
exercise.execution: Lower platform by bending leg until knee is just short of complete flexion. Return by extending knee and hip. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Hack Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Lower seat by flex hips and knees until either is near complete flexion. Raise seat by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Lying Leg Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Push lever platform away by extending hips and knees until knees are straight. Return lever platform by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion or until hips are completely flexed. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Lying Leg Press (custom - plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Push lever platform by extending hips and knees until knees are straight. Lower lever platform by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Single Leg Lying Leg Press (custom - plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Push platform away by extending hip and knee. Return by bending leg until knee or hip is just short of complete flexion. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Leg Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Push platform(s) away by extending knees and hips until knees are fully extended. Return until hips are completely flexed. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Alternating Seated Leg Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Push one platform away by extending knee and hip. Return to original position. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue by alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Lever Single Leg Seated Leg Press (plate loaded)
Lever Single Leg Standing Leg Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Push platform down by extending hip and knee until straight. Return leg to original position. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg positions.

exercise.name: Lever Rear Lunge (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Lever Barbell Rear Lunge (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Lever Single Leg Split Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: With chest high, lift lever by extending hips and knees to full extension. Return until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Barbell Single Leg Split Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Single Leg Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Bend knee forward slightly while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knee pointed same direction of foot. Squat down as low as possible. Extend knee and hip until leg is straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Split Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: With chest high, lift lever by extending hips and knees to full extension. Return until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Barbell Split Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Lower body on other leg by flexing knees and hips of of both legs until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original straddled position by extending hips and knees of both legs. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend by bending knees and hip until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Lift lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend by bending knees and hip until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Lift lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Barbell Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Front Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Lower lever by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Lift lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Full Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until knees and hips are fully bent. Lift lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Hack Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Lower lever by bending hips and knees, until knees are just short of complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever V-Squat (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Bend knees forward slightly while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until hips are just short of complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Leg Extension
exercise.execution: Move lever forward and upward by extending knees until legs are straight. Return lever to original position by bending knees. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Alternating Leg Extension
exercise.execution: Move lever forward and upward by extending one knee until leg is straight. Lower to original position. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue to alternate between sides.

exercise.name: Lever Alternating Leg Extension (unilateral machine)
exercise.execution: Move one lever forward and upward by extending one knee until leg is straight. Lower to original position. Repeat with opposite side. Continue to alternate between sides.

exercise.name: Lever Alternating Lying Leg Press
exercise.execution: Lower one lever platform toward body by bending knee and hip until weight taps or nearly taps unused portion of weight stack. Push lever platform away by extending knee and hip. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue by alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Lever Seated Leg Press
exercise.execution: Extend knees and hips until knees are fully extended. Return until hips are completely flexed. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Single Leg Seated Leg Press
exercise.execution: Push platform away by extending hip and knee. Return by bending leg until knee or hip is just short of complete flexion. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Lever Squat
exercise.execution: Raise lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Lever V-Squat
exercise.execution: Raise lever by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Squat down with knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until knees or hips are near complete flexion. Repeat.

exercise.name: Lever Split V-Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down with knee pointed same direction as foot. Allow leg to bend behind with forefoot on floor. Descend until forward hip is near complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knee and hip until leg is straight. Repeat. Continue with other leg.

exercise.name: Lever Single Leg Split V-Squat
exercise.execution: Raise lever by extending knees and hips. Lower lever by flexing hips and knees until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg positions.

exercise.name: Lever Alternating Single Leg Split V-Squat
exercise.execution: Transfer right foot back to inside of rear vertical platform. Lower lever by flexing hips and knees until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Raise lever by extending knees and hips until knee is straight. Return right foot to original position by other foot. Repeat with opposite leg movement and continue alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Sled 45° Leg Press
exercise.execution: Lower sled by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion or until hips are completely flexed. Return by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Alternating 45° Leg Press
exercise.execution: Lower one platform toward body by bending knee and hip until knees are just short of complete flexion or until hips are completely flexed. Push platform away by extending knee and hip. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue by alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Sled Single Leg 45° Leg Press
exercise.execution: Lower sled by bending leg until knee is just short of complete flexion. Return by extending knee and hip. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Sled Hack Press
exercise.execution: Lower sled by flexing hips and knees until either is near complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Lying Leg Press
exercise.execution: Extend hips and knees. Return until hips are completely flexed. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Lying Leg Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Bring sled toward platform by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion or until hips are completely flexed. Return by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Single Leg Lying Leg Press (plate loaded)
exercise.execution: Bring sled toward platform by flexing hip and knee of supporting leg until knee is just short of complete flexion or until hip is completely flexed. Return by extending knee and hip. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Sled Single Leg Lying Leg Press
exercise.execution: Push platform by extending knee and hip until knee is straight. Return by bending hip and knee of supporting leg until knee is just short of complete flexion or until hip is completely flexed. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Sled Seated Leg Press
exercise.execution: Extend knees and hips until knees are fully extended. Return until hips are completely flexed. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Vertical Leg Press
exercise.execution: Lower sled by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion or just before hips raise up from pad. Return by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Single Leg Vertical Leg Press
exercise.execution: Lower sled by flexing leg until knees are just short of complete flexion or just before hips raise up from pad. Push weight up by extending knee and hip. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Sled Squat
exercise.execution: If hand or lever lock is available, disengage weight, squat to lowest position and re-engage lock. Lift sled by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Lower sled by bending knees forward slightly while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Hack Squat
exercise.execution: Lower sled by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed. Raise sled by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Sled Single Leg Hack Squat
exercise.execution: Lower sled by flexing hips and knee of supporting leg until knees are just short of complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knee and hips. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Sled Rear Lunge
exercise.execution: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs, alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Smith Rear Lunge
exercise.execution: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs, alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Smith Single Leg Split Squat
exercise.execution: Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Smith Split Squat
exercise.execution: Lower body on other leg by flexing knees and hips of both legs until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original straddled position by extending hips and knees of both legs. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Smith Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Single Leg Squat
exercise.execution: Bend knee slightly forward while allowing hips to bend, keeping back straight and knee pointed same direction of foot. Descend until thigh of supporting leg is just past parallel to floor. Extend knee and hip until leg is straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Front Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward , keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Hack Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending knees forward while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are too close to parallel to floor and bar is behind lower leg. Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Wide Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Smith Step Down
exercise.execution: Raise bar upward by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Lower body downward by returning foot off of bench to floor and repeat. Continue with opposite position.

exercise.name: Weighted Belt Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Squat up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Front Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Weighted Single Leg Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Weighted Sissy Squat
exercise.execution: With hips and waist straight, bend knees to allow body to fall backwards as knees come forward. Allow heels to raise from floor. Lower body until knees are almost fully flexed or near floor. Return to original position by extending knees as heels return to floor.

exercise.name: Weighted Sissy Squat (on apparatus)
exercise.execution: Allow body to fall backwards by bending knees. During descent, gradually bend hips, yet keep chest high and don't allow torso to angle forward. Lower body until back of thigh is against upper pad. Rise to original position by extending knees and hips while keeping shoulders behind hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Kettlebell Front Squat
exercise.execution: Bend knees slightly forward while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back taut and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Kettlebell Overhead Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly, until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Clean and Jerk weight with opposite arm and squat with other leg forward.

exercise.name: Kettlebell Overhead Rear Lunge
exercise.execution: Step back with leg on opposite side of kettlebell while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat. Clean and Jerk weight with opposite arm and lunge on other leg.

exercise.name: Rear Lunge
exercise.execution: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Lunge
exercise.execution: Lunge forward with first leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Single Leg Squat (pistol)
exercise.execution: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back as straight as possible and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Single Leg Box Squat (pistol)
exercise.execution: Squat down while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Once bottocks makes contact with bench or box, raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Single Leg Partial Box Squat (pistol)
exercise.execution: Squat down while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Once buttock makes contact with bench or box, raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Single Leg Squat (with leg back)
exercise.execution: Squat down as far as possible while keeping raised leg from contacting floor as far down as possible. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. In lowest position, gently place elevated lower leg on floor. Raise body back up with minimal assistance from raised leg on floor. Stand to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg are straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Single Leg Half Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down to challenging depth while keeping raised leg from contacting floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Stand back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg are straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Single Leg Reclining Squat (bar)
exercise.execution: While reclining back, squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as suppor ting foot. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Sissy Squat
exercise.execution: With hips and waist straight, bend knees to allow body to fall backwards as knees come forward. Allow heels to raise from floor. Lower body until knees are almost fully flexed or near floor. Return to original position by extending knees as heels return to floor.

exercise.name: Sissy Squat (on apparatus)
exercise.execution: Allow body to fall backwards by bending knees. During descent, gradually bend hips, yet keep chest high and don't allow torso to angle forward. Lower body until back of thigh is against upper pad. Rise to original position by extending knees and hips while keeping shoulders behind hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Single Leg Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Squat
