exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Squat up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Half Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend to height which allows prescribed number of reps at suggested intensity, short of thighs descending just past parallel to floor. Stand up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return to standing position and repeat.

exercise.name: Balance Board Squat
exercise.execution: Extend arms forward in front of body. Squat down by bending knees slightly forward while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Squat up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

exercise.name: Step-up
exercise.execution: Place foot of first leg on bench. Stand on bench by extending hip and knee of first leg and place foot of second leg on bench. Step down with second leg by flexing hip and knee of first leg. Return to original standing position by placing foot of first leg to floor. Repeat first step with opposite leg, alternating first steps between legs.

exercise.name: Lateral Step-up
exercise.execution: Lift leg and place foot on bench to side and forward of straight knee. Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning feet to original position. Repeat with opposite leg, alternating between legs.

exercise.name: Step-down
exercise.execution: Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning foot off of bench to floor and repeat. Continue with opposite position.

exercise.name: Alternating Step Down
exercise.execution: Step down with first foot to side of elevated surface onto floor. Stand back up on elevated surface by straightening upper leg and pushing body upward. Place foot to original position, next to opposite foot. Step down and back up with opposite leg in same manner. Repeat by alternating between sides.

exercise.name: Self-assisted Single Leg Squat (bar)
exercise.execution: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as supporting foot. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Self-assisted Single Leg Reclining Squat (pole)
exercise.execution: Squat down while keeping leg elevated off of floor. With arms slightly flexed, lean back slightly while only allowing knee to travel slightly forward. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as supporting foot. Descend to lowest position. Raise body back up to original position while keeping knee behind bar and arms slightly flexed until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Self-assisted Single Leg Squat (leg wrapped)
exercise.execution: Squat down by bending knee forward and hip back behind. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Descend until thigh is just past parallel to floor. Return to standing position with minimal assistance from wrapped leg. Stand to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg are straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Self-assisted Squat
exercise.execution: While holding onto horizontal bar, squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return to standing position and repeat.

exercise.name: Self-assisted Squat (on suspension trainer)
exercise.execution: While holding onto suspension trainer handles, squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return to standing position and repeat.

exercise.name: Self-assisted Squat (on suspension trainer)
exercise.execution: While holding onto suspension trainer handles, squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return to standing position and repeat.

exercise.name: Self-assisted Step-down
exercise.execution: Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning foot off of bench to floor and repeat. Continue with opposite position.

exercise.name: Suspended Reclining Squat
exercise.execution: While reclined back and holding onto suspension trainer handles, squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward while keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are perpendicular to body's angle of movement. Stand up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return to reclined standing position with body straight. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Single Leg Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back, up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Suspended Single Leg Split Squat
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Suspended Single Leg Split Squat (self-assisted)
exercise.execution: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of supporting leg. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

exercise.name: Kneeling Quadriceps Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Drive hip forward and pull foot toward rear end. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Lever Quadriceps Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Squat down with back straight and chest up while positioning hip straight close to back of heel. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Lying (prone) Quadriceps Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Pull ankle or forefoot to rear end. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: PNF Lying (prone) Quadriceps Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Lift knee and push ankle down toward hip. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Lying (side) Quadriceps Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Straighten hip by moving knee backward. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Seated Quadriceps Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Pull ankle or forefoot to rear end and straighten hip by moving knee backwards. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Standing Quadriceps Stretch
exercise.mechanic: Pull ankle or forefoot to rear end and straighten hip by moving knee backward. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Standing Quadriceps Stretch (towel)

exercise.name: Standing Quadriceps Stretch (on apparatus)
exercise.mechanic: Bend supporting knee slightly while positioning hip back closer to heel. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

exercise.name: Standing Quadriceps Stretch (on platform)

exercise.name: Butt Kick

exercise.name: Barbell Good-morning
exercise.execution: Keeping back straight, bend hips to lower torso forward until parallel to floor. Raise torso until hips are extended. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Glute-Ham Raise
exercise.execution: From lower position, raise torso by extending hips until fully extended. Continue to raise body by flexing knees until body is upright. Lower body by straightening knees until body is horizontal. Continue to lower torso by bending hips until body is upside down. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Inverse Leg Curl
exercise.execution: Lower body until horizontal by straightening knees. Raise body by flexing knees only allowing hips to bend slightly. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Hyperextension

exercise.name: Barbell Back Raise (on hyperextension apparatus)

exercise.name: Barbell 45° Hyperextension

exercise.name: Barbell 45° Back Raise (on hyperextension apparatus)

exercise.name: Barbell Straight Leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: With knees straight, lower bar toward top of feet by bending hips and waist. Lift bar by extending waist and hip until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

exercise.name: Barbell Straight-back Straight-leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: With knees and back straight, lower bar by bending hips until hamstrings are tight, or just before lower back bends. Lift bar by extending hips until upright. Pull shoulders slightly back at top of lift if rounded. Repeat.

exercise.name: Trap Bar Straight Leg Deadlift

Set weight on floor. Lift bar by extending waist and hip until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

exercise.name: Trap Bar Straight-back Straight-leg Deadlift

exercise.name: Cable Lying Leg Curl

exercise.name: Cable Standing Leg Curl

exercise.name: Cable Straight Leg Deadlift

exercise.name: Cable Straight-back Straight-leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: With knees and back straight, bow forward by bending hips until hamstrings are tight, or just before lower back bends. Raise body upright by extending hips until standing. Pull shoulders back slightly at top of lift if rounded. Repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Straight Leg Deadlift
exercise.execution: With knees straight, lower dumbbells to top or sides of feet by bending hips. Allow hips to fall back and bend waist as dumbbell approaches feet. Lift dumbbells by extending hips and waist until standing upright. Pull shoulders back if rounded. Repeat.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Straight-back Straight-leg Deadlift

exercise.name: Romanian Deadlift
exercise.execution: Lower bar toward top of feet by bending hips while tracing front contour of legs through downward motion. Gradually bend knees through descent and keep spine straight so back is near horizontal at lowest position. Once hamstring is stretched fully just before lowering bar to completely to floor, lift bar by extending hips and knees until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

exercise.name: Hanging Hamstring Bridge
exercise.execution: Raise hips up as high as possible by extending hips. Lower hips to original position just above floor. Repeat.

exercise.name: Single Leg Hanging Hamstring Bridge
exercise.execution: Raise hips up as high as possible by extending hip and spine. Maintain bent position of lower leg allowing it to rise with hips. Lower hips along with bent lower leg to original position and repeat. Continue with legs in opposite position.

Hanging Leg Curl
exercise.execution: Pull body toward feet by bending knees and hips. Roll onto feet until knees are fully flexed. Return body to original position by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Hanging Straight Hip Leg Curl
exercise.execution: Pull body toward feet by bending knees while keeping hips straight. Roll onto feet until knees are fully flexed. Return body to original position by extending knees. Repeat.

exercise.name: Inverse Leg Curl
exercise.execution: Lower body until horizontal by straightening knees. Raise body by flexing knees only allowing hips to bend slightly. Repeat.

exercise.name: Straight Hip Leg Curl (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Keeping hips and low back straight, bend knees, pulling heels toward rear end. Allow feet to rollup on to ball. Lower to original position by straightening knees. Repeat.

exercise.name: Single Leg Straight Hip Leg Curl (on stability ball)
exercise.execution: Keeping hips and low back straight, bend knee, pulling heel toward rear end while keeping other leg extended straight so it raises upward. Allow foot to rollup on to ball. Lower to original position by straightening knee until other leg makes contact with ball. Repeat.

exercise.name: Leg Curl (on power wheel)
exercise.execution: Keeping hips and low back straight, bend knees, pulling heels toward rear end. Raise up until lower legs are vertical. Lower to original position by straightening knees. Repeat.

exercise.name: Self-assisted Inverse Leg Curl
exercise.execution: Lower body with hips straight by slowly straightening knees. Position hands forward, ready to push body weight back up off of surface. Control descent only with hamstrings as low as possible before catching body by quickly placing hands on elevated platform and rapidly pushing off against platform, just enough to assist hamstrings in raising body upward. Return to upright kneeling position and repeat.

exercise.name: Self-assisted Inverse Leg Curl (on floor)
exercise.execution: Lower body with hips straight by slowly straightening knees. Control descent only with hamstrings as low as possible. Only when body begins to fall, touch down with tensed finger tips out to each side. Once fingers make contact with floor, control remaining descent with assistance of arms. Allowing chest to come very close to floor, rapidly push off against floor, again just enough to assist hamstrings in raising body upward. Return to upright kneeling position and repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Leg Curl
exercise.execution: Pull heels toward rear end by bending knees and hips simultaneously. Lower body to original position by straightening knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Hamstring Runner
exercise.execution: Simultaneously alternate leg positions by straightening bent leg while bending straight knee. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Hanging Leg Curl
exercise.execution: Pull body toward feet by bending knees and hips. Roll onto feet until knees are fully flexed. Return body to original position by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Hanging Straight Hip Leg Curl
exercise.execution: Pull body toward feet by bending knees while keeping hips and back straight. Roll onto feet until knees are fully flexed. Return body to original position by extending knees maintaining straight hip position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Hyperextension
exercise.execution: Drive hips forward until hips are straight, while keeping arms and shoulders straight. Near top of motion, reach back with arms over head and hyperextend spine. While keeping arms over head, lower body with hips falling back down to starting position and repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Straight Hip Leg Curl
exercise.execution: Bend knees, pulling heels toward rear end while keeping hips and low back straight. Raise up until lower legs are vertical or fully flexed. Lower body to original position by straightening knees, maintaining straight hip position. Repeat.

exercise.name: Suspended Single Leg Straight Hip Leg Curl (on bench)
exercise.execution: Bend knee of leg in suspension trainer while keeping other leg extended. Continue pulling heel toward rear end while keeping hips and low back straight. Raise up until lower leg is vertical or fully flexed. Lower body to original position by straightening knee until leg is straight and next to extended leg, maintaining straight hip position throughout movement. Repeat.
